(168, '2021-02-25', '2021-02-25', 'On Muhammad Ali Becoming The World Heavy Weight Boxing Champion Of The World.', 'In 1964, Cassius Clay Jr, who will later be known be known as Muhammad Ali, became the world\'s Heavyweight Boxing Champion of the World. <br/><br/>\r\n\r\n That was after the 22-year old underdog knocked out undisputed champion Sonny Liston at the seventh round of their title fight held in Miami Beach. Starting to box at 12 years old, he won the international Golden Gloves heavyweight title at the age of 17; and the 1960 Olympic Games light heavyweight gold in Rome. <br/><br/>\r\n\r\n Two days after surprising the world with his triumph, he announced that he\'d join Islam changed his name to Muhammad Ali. He\'d become the 20th century\'s greatest sporting figures.', 'May sports produce more champions and celebrities who have something worthwhile for their advocacy. May Filipinos produce more world champion boxers and athletes.', 'Everyone who competes in the games goes into strict training. They do it to get a crown that will not last, but we do it to get a crown that will last forever. 26 Therefore I do not run like someone running aimlessly; I do not fight like a boxer beating the air. 27 No, I strike a blow to my body and make it my slave so that after I have preached to others, I myself will not be disqualified for the prize. <br/>\r\n- <b> 1 Corinthians 9:25-27 </b>', '<i>In human history, we can see sparkles of God\'s redeeming stories</i><br/>\r\n- Pastor Jose Tacadena', 'https://bit.ly/3qK8yMc', 0, NULL, 'While literal sports is challenging, its spiritual implications are more vital.'),
(169, '2021-02-25', '2021-02-25', 'On Philippines Having Two Opposing Presidents At The Same Time.', 'In 1986, the Philippines have two opposing presidents at the same times. <br/><br/>\r\n\r\n Corazon Aquino was proclaimed president at the Club Filipino in San Juan, Metro Manila by virtue of the Philippine Revolution. She was sworn in by Supreme Court Senior Justice Claudio Teehankee to lead the provisional government. <br/><br/>\r\n\r\n Ferdinand Marcos was sworn in as president an hour later inside Malacañang. He took his oath under the 1973 Constitution by Chief Justice Roman Aquino. <br/><br/>\r\n\r\n It was a terrible situation that would have taken much time and cost countless lives. But by the end of that day, Pres. Marcos and his family hastily left Malacañang on board US choppers. Pleaded by US President Ronald Reagan to quit, they eventually flew to Hawaii.', 'May our elections, especially the presidential always turn out fair, just and efficient, with the real winners being proclaimed swiftly.', 'He changes times and seasons; he deposes kings and raises up others. He gives wisdom to the wise and knowledge to the discerning. <br/>\r\n–<b> Daniel 2:21 </b>', '<i>In human history, we can see sparkles of God\'s redeeming stories</i><br/>\r\n- Pastor Jose Tacadena', 'https://bit.ly/39aBKGk', 1, NULL, 'Amidst the terrors and turmoil of the society and the bloody mess that dirty politics cause from time to time, it is reassuring that God remains sovereign.'),
(170, '2021-02-26', '2021-02-26', 'On Arrival Of First Batch Of South Korean Troops In Saigon.', 'In 1965, the first batch of South Korean troops arrived in Saigon, Vietnam to help the South Vietnamese against the communist North. <br/><br/>\r\n\r\n This was a part of Free World Military forces, soldiers from nations allied to the USA and South Vietnam which was being attacked by communists then. <br/><br/>\r\n\r\n This allied group was an effort by US Pres. Lyndon Johnson who hoped to build an international consensus support of the American policies in Vietnam. The South Koreans sent a total of 47, 800 soldiers there by the end of 1969. They began to withdraw in February, 1972.', 'May Vietnam continue to develop economically, politically and spiritually. May it cease from persecuting its Christian citizens and missionaries. May Korea continue to progress on all fronts and be rewarded for its readiness to help other countries.', '16 And do not forget to do good and to share with others, for with such sacrifices God is pleased. <br/>\r\n- <b> Hebrews 13:16 </b>', '<i>In human history, we can see sparkles of God\'s redeeming stories</i><br/>\r\n- Pastor Jose Tacadena', 'https://bit.ly/3qK8yMc', 0, NULL, 'That Korea is a much smaller nation than the US, and still helped the Americans on its plan, is a good challenge for each of us to continue assisting each other.'),
(171, '2021-02-26', '2021-02-26', 'On Apolinario Mabini Taking Oath Of Allegiance To The U.S. Before The American Collector Of Customs.', 'In 1903, Apolinario Mabini   took oath of allegiance to the United States before the American Collector of Customs. <br/><br/>\r\n\r\n Before that, Mabini was the main Constitutional adviser to the Filipino Revolutionary Government and the first Prime Minister of the Philippines with the creation of the Malolos Republic. <br/><br/>\r\n\r\n He\'s captured by the Americans in December, 1899. When he refused to swear allegiance to the US government even with incentive offers, he was deported to Guam. <br/><br/>\r\n\r\n After two years of homesickness and weakening body and wanting to go back to his motherland, he finally succumbed to pressure and swore allegiance to the US government, an American condition for allowing his return.', 'May we remember and emulate Mabini\'s heroism and nationalism. May Filipino Overseas Workers overcome the temptation of homesickness and other problems. May they bring honor to their motherland wherever they may be.', 'He changes times and seasons; he deposes kings and raises up others. He gives wisdom to the wise and knowledge to the discerning. <br/>\r\n–<b> Daniel 2:21 </b>', '<i>In human history, we can see sparkles of God\'s redeeming stories</i><br/>\r\n- Pastor Jose Tacadena', 'https://bit.ly/368XEYA', 1, NULL, 'Amidst the terrors and turmoils of the society and the bloody mess that dirty politics cause from time to time, it is reassuring that God remains sovereign.');











