INSERT INTO `glimpse` (`id`, `title`, `glimpse_date`, `heading`, `content`, `prayer_focus`, `featured_verse`, `featured_quote`, `image_link`, `type`, `created_at`, `transition`) VALUES
(63, '2021-01-05', '2021-01-05', 'On the Beginning of the Construction of the Golden Gate Bridge the USA', 'In 1933, the golden gate bridge construction begun.<br/><br/>\r\n\r\nThis was after workers started excavating 3.25 million cubic feet of dirt for the structure\'s big anchorage.  The plan to build the bridge that would connect the San Francisco Peninsula with the southern end of Marin country begun in 1849 after the Gold rush in the land north of San Francisco.<br/><br/>\r\n\r\nCity engineer <i>Michael O\'Shaughnessy</i> who also named the gate, and <i>Joseph Strauss</i>, another engineer and poet, took charge of the construction that cost around US $30 million and took four years to finish.<br/><br/>\r\n\r\nIt officially opened on <i>May 27, 1937</i> eventually becoming a world famous American landmark and tourist spot.\r\n', 'May the <i>Golden Gate Bridge</i> and all the other (major) bridges the world over be properly maintained and enhanced to survive massive earthquakes and flooding. <br/><br/>\r\n\r\nMay more vital bridges be built where strategic and truly needed.', 'Jesus answered, <i>"I am the way the truth and the life. No one comes to the father except through me."</i><br/>\r\n- <b>John 14.6</b>', '<i>In human history, we can see sparkles of God\'s redeeming stories</i><br/>\r\n- Pastor Jose Tacadena', 'https://www.history.com/.image/ar_1:1%2Cc_fill%2Ccs_srgb%2Cfl_progressive%2Cq_auto:good%2Cw_1200/MTY1MTc3MjE0MzExMDgxNTQ1/topic-golden-gate-bridge-gettyimages-177770941.jpg', 0, NULL, 'While human bridges are mostly helpful for connecting locations and people, the spiritual bridge who is the Lord Jesus is certainly millions better on all fronts. We must appreciate the Lord Jesus connecting us to God the father.<br/><br/>'),
(64, '2021-01-05', '2021-01-05', 'In 2011, Senator Antonio Trillanes IV and 18 other Magdalo Officers formally applied for Amnesty.', 'Senator Antonio Trillanes IV and other members of the Magdalo group pose for a <i>Group Shot</i> after applying for government amnesty before the Department of National Defense amnesty committee at <i>Camp Aguinaldo</i>.<br/><br/>\r\n\r\nThey sent their application to the <i>Department of National Defense (DND) Ad Hoc Committee</i> in <i>Camp Aguinaldo, Quezon City.</i><br/><br/>\r\n\r\nTrillanes was one of the leaders of the 2003 Oakwoood Mutiny where they lmabdasted the supposed corruption of the President Gloria Arroyo Administration. <br/><br/>\r\n\r\nIn 2007, he walked out of the Camp Crame Custodial Center after the Makti Regional Trial Court and staged the Manila Peninsula Hotel Siege.<br/><br/>\r\n\r\nIn December 2010, he was given provisional liberty, and a year later was given amnesty by then President Noynoy Aquino. <br/><br/>', 'May God\'s truth, fairness, and justice prevail in Senator Trillanes\' pending case by the Department of Justice. May every government refrain from using their power to unjustly harass their critics.', '<i>"And that is what some of you were. \r\nBut you were washed, you were sanctified, you were justified in the name of the Lord Jesus Christ and the Spirit of our God."</i><br>\r\n- <b>Romans 8:1</b>', '<i>"In human history, we can see sparkles of God\'s redeeming stories"</i>\r\n- Pastor Jose Tacadena', 'https://www8.gmanews.tv/webpics/infotech/trillanesamnesty1.jpg', 1, NULL, 'While government amnesty may be considered a great blessing to those who receive it, how much more should God\'s own version of Amnesty? The Bible calls it justification and is given to those who receive Jesus as their personal and Lord and Savior.  We must strive to reciprocate God justifying us by living for him. <br/>'),
(69, '2021-01-06', '2021-01-06', 'In 1812, <i>Melchora Aquino de Ramos,</i> known as <i>Tandang Sora,</i> was born in Balintawak.', 'Even while already 84 years old, she opened her house to the Katipuneros led by <i>Andres Bonifacio</i>. She provided the revolutionaries food, clothing and shelter. Because of this, she was arrested by Guardia Civil in Barrio Pasong Putik, Novaliches and gailed in Bilibid Prison in Manila. She was even exiled to Guam where she lived as a servant. She came back to the Philippines in 1903, at 91 years old, and died at 107 in 1919.', 'May we not forget her heroism as well as those who have sacrificed for the freedom of the Philippines against tyrants. May we continue to respect the elderlies and give them enough space to continue experiencing self actualization and to bless other people through their talents, skills and experience and passion.', 'Many women were there, watching from a distance. They had followed Jesus from Galilee to care for his needs. Among them were Mary Magdalene, Mary the mother of James and Joseph, and the mother of Zebedee\'s sons.<br/>\r\n- Matthew 27:55-56', 'In human history, we can see sparkles of God\'s redeeming stories.<br/>\r\n- Pastor Jose Tacadena', 'https://kahimyang.com/resources/tandang_sora.webp', 1, NULL, 'Do you know that even our dear Lord Jesus Christ and his apostles were ministered by numerous women of various ages and background? We must strive to respect and appreciate the women in our society.'),
(68, '2021-01-06', '2021-01-06', 'In 1838, <i>Samuel Morse\'s</i> telegraph system was demonstrated in public for the first time.<br/><br/>', 'This happened at the <i>Speedwell Iron Works</i> in <i>Morristown, New Jersey.</i>  His device used electric impulses to transmit encoded messages over a wire.<br/><br/>\r\nIn 1843, he convinced the US Congress to fund the construction of the first telegraph line in the country - from <i>Washington, DC to Baltimore.</i> In 1844, the Massachusetts-born Morse sent his first official telegram over the line. His message, <b>"What hat God wrought!"</b>', 'May telegraph and the more modern means of communication, especially the internet, be developed further, and be more accessible even to the third world countries and marginalized people.', '"Now to him who is able to do immeasurably more than all we ask or imaging, according to his power that is at work within us, to him be glory in the church and in Christ Jesus throughout all generations, for ever and ever! Amen."<br/>\r\n- Ephesians 3:20-21', '"In human history, we can see sparkles of God\'s redeeming stories"<br/>\r\n- Pastor Jose Tacadena', 'https://encrypted-tbn0.gstatic.com/images?q=tbn:ANd9GcTepj4E0HfrDPWrhFYaIk-BqeRtuJUS3BtKdQ&usqp=CAU', 0, NULL, 'It\'s heartwarming that Morse attributed his great invention in part to God\'s working through his ability and knowledge. More than the telegraph, God not only receives but amplifies our communication to the point of blessing us beyond our abilities, good intentions and passion. So, he deserves our praise for our every achievement. We must strive to honor God for every enabling He has given us to achieve in life.'),
(70, '2021-01-07', '2021-01-07', 'In 1789, the first presidential election in the United States of America was held.', 'Only white men who owned property were allowed to vote. Early favorite George Washington won the election unanimously as all 69 electors chose him. John Adams won as the first vice president.<br/><br/>\r\nHe was sworn as the first president of the USA on April 30, 1789. He was later unanimously re-elected in 1792 for another term and ended his tenure on March 7, 1797.', 'May the USA continue to be a model of democracy and fair elections.<br/>\r\nMay the citizens be wiser in electing their national leaders. While the election candidates be more qualified and responsible to the position they are vying for.', 'Therefore, my brothers and sisters, make every effort to confirm your calling and election. For if you do these things, you will never stumble.<br/>\r\n- <b>2 Peter 1:10</b><br/><br/>\r\n\r\nYou did not choose me, but I chose you and appointed you so that you might go and bear fruit - fruit that will last.<br/>\r\n- <b>John 15:6</b>', 'In human history, we can see sparkles of God\'s redeeming stories.<br/>\r\n- Pastor Jose Tacadena', 'https://www.biography.com/.image/t_share/MTY2NDcwODAyODk0NDk2OTI5/gilbert_stuart_williamstown_portrait_of_george_washington_promo.jpg', 0, NULL, 'Do you know that in a way, the Lord Jesus Christ has elected Christians? We must strive to deserve somehow God choosing us to grow in our faith.'),
(71, '2021-01-07', '2021-01-07', 'In 1901, Major general Arthur MacArthur Jr. Ordered the deportation of leaders of the Philippine revolution against the USA to Guam.', 'MacArthur Jr. was the military Governor-General of the American occupied Philippines.<br/><br/>\r\nHe particularly detested Apolinario Mabini for leading the Filipino revolutionaries. Mabini was the chief adviser of Gen. Emilio Aguinaldo, who wrote the "True Decalogue" which inspired the Filipinos to fight and die for freedom.<br/><br/>\r\nMabini sailed to Guam along with 31 others including Pablo Ocampo, Pio del Pilar, and Gen. Artemio Ricarte.', 'May deportees be protected from all sorts of abuse by citizens of their host countries, while the former learn to adjust to the foreigners\' culture and be better qualified and equipped to return home. May God continue to bless our overseas Filipino workers everywhere.', 'When a foreigner resides among you in your land, do not mistreat them. The foreigner residing among you must be treated as your native born. Love them as yourself, for you were foreigners in Egypt. I am the Lord your God.<br/><br/>\r\n- Leviticus 19:33-34', 'In human history, we can see sparkles of God\'s redeeming stories.<br/>\r\n- Pastor Jose Tacadena', 'https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/f/fb/Arthur_MacArthur_Jr.jpg', 1, NULL, 'The reality of people being deported or voluntarily journeying abroad moved God to remind us to treat foreigners properly. We must strive to treat aliens and visitors well.'),
(72, '2021-01-08', '2021-01-08', 'On the death of Galileo Galilei, the father of modern astronomy and the father of modern physics.', 'In 1642, Italian astronomer Galileo Galilei died in Italy at 77 years old.<br/><br/>\r\nRecognized as the Father of Modern Astronomy and the Father of Modern Physics. Due to his revolutionary discoveries, Galileo was the first person to use the telescope to observe the skies. He discovered the moons of Jupiter, the rings of Saturn, sunspots and solar rotation.<br/><br/>\r\nHe later published his confirmation that the earth orbits the sun. For this, he was tried and found guilty by the inquisition (the legal body of the Catholic Church) of heresy and was sentenced to life imprisonment in 1633, (which was downgraded to lifetime house arrest).', 'May religious leaders do not reject truly scientific realities; and may scientist and other Science-based people do not ridicule spiritual realities.<br/><br/>\r\nMay more scientists discover and invent more truly useful things and realities.\r\nMay they become more open to the Creator', 'He who made the pleiades and orion, who turns midnight into dawnland darkens day into night, who calls for the waters of the sea and pours them out over the face of the land - The Lord is His name.<br/>\r\n- Amos 5:8', '', 'https://images.saymedia-content.com/.image/t_share/MTc1Nzg1MTc0NDUyMzQ3OTU5/galileo-galilei-discovers-the-moons-of-jupiter-and-the-phase-of-venus.jpg', 0, NULL, 'While we may be amazed at the wonderful creations above and beyond us - we must be cognizant of the Supreme One who made all of these.<br/>\r\nWe must strive to recognize that God, indeed created all natural creations.'),
(73, '2021-01-08', '2021-01-08', 'In 2016, then 82-year old German Molina Moreno, better known as Kuya Germs and the "Master Showman" died due to Cardiac arrest.', 'This Spanish-Filipino TV host, actor-comedian and talent manager was a former teen vendor and jeepney barker. He got into showbiz when he started to work as a janitor and curtain raiser at the Clover Leaf theater in 1957.<br/><br/>\r\nHe got his first break when he was chosen to portray the role of Jesus Christ for the Manila Grand Opera. He then became a comedian for Sampaguita Pictures, home of the biggest starts at that time.<br/><br/>\r\nHis biggest break came as a host of the Sunday noontime variety show, GMA Supershow in the late 1970s, and later as the host, star-builder and producer of "That\'s Entertainment", which discovered and developed the most famous stars in the Philippine entertainment industry then.', 'May more sincere and helpful star-builders and talent managers rise up at the Philippine Entertainment Industry. May sexual harassment, bullying and all the other forms of abuse be prevented in this industry.<br/><br/>\r\nMay those truly deserving artists be given the ample chance to be recognized.', 'We who are strong ought to bear with the failings of the weak and not to please ourselves. Each of us should please our neighbors for their good, to build them up.<br/><br/>\r\n- Romans 15:1-2', '', 'https://contents.pep.ph/images2/2018/10/04/kuya-germs-main.jpg', 1, NULL, 'Not only the talent managers, but everyone of us are commanded to be sincere in building up others, especially those who are weaker than us. We must strive to empathize and help those who are weak and in the need.'),
(74, '2021-01-09', '2021-01-09', 'On The Unveiling Of The Iphone By Steve Jobs', 'In 2007, Steve Jobs unveiled the iPhone, the touch screen mobile phone with an iPod, camera and web-browsing features.<br/><br/>\r\n\r\nIn its unveiling that happened in MacWorld Convention in San Francisco, Jobs claimed that his revolutionary and magical products is literally five years ahead than any other phone. <br/><br/>\r\n\r\n In November, Time Magazine named the iPhone, which in ten months had sale of 1.4 million already, the<i>"Invention of the Year"</i>. <br/><br/>\r\n\r\n In 2012, more than 200 million phones had been sold, making the Apple which Jobs co-founded in 1976, into one of the Earth\'s most valuable corporations.\r\n', 'May more advanced and efficiently useful gadgets and equipment be invented at more affordable costs. May we all be good stewards of such tools and refrain from using them only for our own enjoyment.', 'We proclaim to you what we have seen and heard, so that you also may have fellowship with us. And our fellowship is with the Father and with his Son, Jesus Christ. <br/>\r\n- <b>1 John 1:3</b>', '<i>In human history, we can see sparkles of God\'s redeeming stories</i><br/>\r\n- Pastor Jose Tacadena', 'https://bit.ly/3nrJGXq', 0, NULL, 'While inventions like iPhones connect people faster and more conveniently, studies have shown that these actually devalue meaningful communications with them. We must go back to the basic of communication with God and others through fellowship  - having in-depth communication with them that lead to better and spiritual relationships. We must strive to help in fostering better communication and bonding with others.'),
(75, '2021-01-09', '2021-01-09', 'On The Establishment Of The Barter Trade Zone In Mindanao', 'In 1973, a barter trade zone was established in Mindanao. <br/><br/>\r\n\r\n This was through Presidential Decree No. 93, signed by then Pres. Ferdinand Marcos. It allowed businessmen from the Sulu Archipelago to trade with neighboring islands and sell imported items within the region without tariff duties. <br/><br/>\r\n\r\n In this way, the Filipinos can buy imported items, especially electronic gadgets and equipments at relatively low prices.', 'May the government\'s plan to revive the barter trade zone in Mindanao this year succeeded.', 'So in everything, do to others what you would have them do to you, for this sums up the Law and the Prophets.<br/>\r\n–<b>Matthew 7:12</b>', '<i>In human history, we can see sparkles of God\'s redeeming stories</i><br/>\r\n- Pastor Jose Tacadena', 'https://bit.ly/2LcKbaW', 1, NULL, 'There is a much better barter trade than economic goods. This is called by many as the Golden Rule. We must strive to apply God\'s Golden Rule.'),
(76, '2021-01-10', '2021-01-10', 'On The Convening of the United Nations Assembly', 'In 1946, the first general assembly of the United Nations was convened at the Westminster Central Hall in London, England.<br/><br/>\r\n\r\n Fifty-one nations took part in this. A week later, the UN Security Council had its initial gathering, establishing its rules of procedure.<br/><br/>\r\n\r\n On Jan 24, the General Assembly passed its first resolution. It called for peaceful uses of atomic energy and the cessation of atomic and other weapons of mass destruction.<br/><br/>\r\n\r\n', 'May the United Nations succeed in its goal of maintaining peace and order in the world, and in restraining uncooperative nations.', 'I appeal to you, brothers and sisters, in the name of our Lord Jesus Christ, that all of you agree with one another in what you say and that there be no divisions among you, but that you be perfectly united in mind and thought. <br/>\r\n- <b>1 Corinthians 1:10</b>', '<i>In human history, we can see sparkles of God\'s redeeming stories</i><br/>\r\n- Pastor Jose Tacadena', 'https://bit.ly/3pY4kjE', 0, NULL, 'Unity is an integral part to genuine peace and progress. No wonder God has commanded Christians to apply it themselves. We must strive to be united with the people around us.'),
(77, '2021-01-10', '2021-01-10', 'On The Signing Into Law of the First Comprehensive Local Government Code', 'In 1983, the Philippines\' first comprehensive local government code was signed into law. <br/><br/>\r\n\r\n This was through Batas Pambansa Bilang 337 signed by Pres. Ferdinand Marcos. The code defined the power and functions of local elective officials, giving them authority while decentralizing government powers in barangays, towns, cities and provinces. <br/><br/>\r\n\r\n The city of local government was tasked to maintain coordination and consultative arrangements with other ministers and national government offices.', 'May the new local government code of the Philippines be maximized to the full benefit of the Filipinos all over the country through its local government units. May the local government be truly sensitive to the needs of their people and effective in meeting them.', 'Submit yourselves for the Lord\'s sake to every human authority: whether to the emperor, as the supreme authority, 14 or to governors, who are sent by him to punish those who do wrong and to commend those who do right.<br/>\r\n–<b>1 Peter 2:13-14</b>', '<i>In human history, we can see sparkles of God\'s redeeming stories</i><br/>\r\n- Pastor Jose Tacadena', 'https://bit.ly/3i5EKXq', 1, NULL, 'While well thought about local government codes are helpful, it is always the citizen\'s cooperation which is the key to community progress. We must strive to respect and submit to our national and local government leaders.'),
(78, '2021-01-11', '2021-01-11', 'On US Pres. Theodore Roosevelt Making the Grand Canyon a National Park', 'In 1908, US Pres. Theodore Roosevelt made Grand Canyon a national park. <br/><br/>\r\n\r\n Located in Northwestern Arizona, Grand Canyon was first explored in 1869 by geologist John Wesley Powell and his team of ten men. <br/><br/>\r\n\r\n By declaring the Grand Canyon as a national park, all private development of the land was banned. The outlawing of private development became official only in 1919 when Pres. Woodrow Wilson signed the Grand Canyon National Park Act</i>. <br/><br/>\r\n\r\n Today, more than 5 million people visit the canyon yearly. \r\n', 'May the Grand Canyon and other national parks in the world continue to be protected by both the government and private sector.', 'How many are your works, Lord! In wisdom you made them all; the earth is full of your creatures. May the glory of the Lord endure forever; may the Lord rejoice in his works. <br/>\r\n- <b> Psalm 104:24, 31</b>', '<i>In human history, we can see sparkles of God\'s redeeming stories</i><br/>\r\n- Pastor Jose Tacadena', 'https://bit.ly/3q2YBZP', 0, NULL, 'May we all admit that the natural resources are created by our great God who deserves our recognition and worship.'),
(79, '2021-01-11', '2021-01-11', 'On The Inauguration Of The First Geothermal Power Plant', 'In 1979, the first geothermal power plant in the Philippines was inaugurated in Tiwi, Albay. <br/><br/>\r\n\r\n This is the third largest geothermal facility in the country with 275 megawatts of installed generating capacity. The government decision to build such plant is based on Republic Act No. 5092 or the Geothermal Law enacted in 1967. It stipulated that natural gases and geothermal energy resources belong to the State and enabled the government to set aside land as geothermal reservations. <br/><br/>\r\n\r\n In 1970, Presidential Decree No. 739 established 17, 661 hectares in Albay Province to constitute the Tiwi geothermal reservations.', 'May the government enhance its program of developing geothermal energy and using it to the maximum. May more resources of natural energy in the country be discovered. May existing plants continue to abound with this energy.', '<i>But you will receive power when the Holy Spirit comes on you; and you will be my witnesses in Jerusalem, and in all Judea and Samaria, and to the ends of the earth.</i><br/>\r\n–<b>Acts 1:8</b><br/>\r\nFor the Spirit God gave us does not make us timid, but gives us power, love and self-discipline.<br/>\r\n–<b>2 Timothy 1:7</b>', '<i>In human history, we can see sparkles of God\'s redeeming stories</i><br/>\r\n- Pastor Jose Tacadena', 'https://bit.ly/2LcKbaW', 1, NULL, 'While its beneficial to discover, develop and use natural energy, we must not forget that the greatest energy is available to Christians.'),
(80, '2021-01-12', '2021-01-12', 'On The Restoration of the Great Pyramid in Egypt.', 'In 1984, the restoration of Egypt\'s Great Pyramid finally took a turn after years of failed efforts. <br/><br/>\r\n\r\n This was after the international panel overseeing the restoration of the Great Pyramid abandoned modern construction technique of using mortar and water-based cement. <br/><br/>\r\n\r\n As they discovered after about three years of trying, water in modern cement caused adjacent limestone to split, damaging the pyramid structure little by little. <br/><br/>\r\n\r\n Resorting to the method used by ancient Egyptians, they simply interlocked blocks. Though that process was tedious and took longer, it was the key to eventually restoring the entire pyramid.\r\n', 'May the pyramids of Egypt continue to be well taken care of and be protected from vandals and thieves.', 'They found the stone rolled away from the tomb, 3 but when they entered, they did not find the body of the Lord Jesus. <br/>\r\n- <b>1 John 1:3</b>', '<i>In human history, we can see sparkles of God\'s redeeming stories</i><br/>\r\n- Pastor Jose Tacadena', 'https://bit.ly/2LFmTKv', 0, NULL, 'While the pyramids are pompous or extravagant, they remain burial sites of skeletal remains. Jesus Christ\'s tomb may be simple and impoverished but it is empty! For He has risen from the dead and is alive forevermore.'),
(81, '2021-01-12', '2021-01-12', 'On The Formation of the Hispano-Filipino Association in Madrid, Spain', 'In 1889, the Hispano-Filipino Association was formed in Madrid, Spain. <br/><br/>\r\n\r\n Composed of Filipino and Spaniards, it called for reforms in the Philippines during the Spanish colonization. <br/><br/>\r\n\r\n It specifically campaigned for Filipino representations in the Spanish Cortes and the passage of Maura Law so educational reforms could take place in the Philippines. Among the Filipino members were Graciano Lopez Jaena, Marcelo del Pilar, Antonio Luna, Mariano Ponce and Jose Rizal. Spanish members included Miguel Morayta, a history professor at the Universidad Central de Madrid.', 'May the Filipinos in nations where they work or live organize or try to join alliances with foreigners to promote the welfare of the Philippines. May the Philippine embassies worldwide become effective tools of our nation, government and people.', 'You are to have the same law for the foreigner and the native-born. I am the Lord your God.<br/>\r\n–<b>Leviticus 24:22</b>', '<i>In human history, we can see sparkles of God\'s redeeming stories</i><br/>\r\n- Pastor Jose Tacadena', 'https://bit.ly/3q3tihv', 1, NULL, 'That people from different races should have fair treatment to each other is embedded in the Bible. After all, we are accountable to one Supreme Maker.'),
(82, '2021-01-13', '2021-01-13', 'On Pope Honorius II Recognizing the Knights Templar as God\'s Army.', 'In 1128, Pope Honorius II officially recognized Knights Templar as a military order, branding it as God\'s Army. <br/><br/>\r\n\r\n Founded by Frenchman, Hughes de Payens in 1118, the Knight Templar aimed to protect Christian pilgrims on their way to and from the Holy Lands during the Crusades. <br/><br/>\r\n\r\n As they discovered after about three years of trying, water in modern cement caused adjacent limestone to split, damaging the pyramid structure little by little. <br/><br/>\r\n\r\n The Templars adhered to rigid rules – must have noble birth, take strict vows of poverty, obedience and charity. By the end of the of the Crusades in the 14th century, the Templars have grown wealthy, provoking the jealousy of both religious and secular powers. Their group was eventually dissolved in 1307 by King Philip IV and Pope Clement V.\r\n', 'May religious groups desist from organizing literal armies and political groups but focus on the spiritual.', 'For our struggle is not against flesh and blood, but against the rulers, against the authorities, against the powers of this dark world and against the spiritual forces of evil in the heavenly realms. 13 Therefore put on the full armor of God, so that when the day of evil comes, you may be able to stand your ground, and after you have done everything, to stand.<br/>\r\n- <b>Ephesians 6:12-13</b>', '<i>In human history, we can see sparkles of God\'s redeeming stories</i><br/>\r\n- Pastor Jose Tacadena', 'https://bit.ly/39iETm5', 0, NULL, 'Do you know that Christians are actually spiritual soldiers who battle Satan and his demon forces? They should wear their spiritual armor always.'),
(83, '2021-01-13', '2021-01-13', 'On the Recognition of Sultan Kudarat Of Maguindanao As A Filipino Hero', 'In 1975, Sultan Kudarat of Maguindanao was officially recognized as a Filipino hero. <br/><br/>\r\n\r\n This was through the Letter of Instruction 126 by President Ferdinand Marcos and the the making of Sultan Kudarat commemorative stamps that were presented to the descendants of the hero. Kudarat was a direct descendant of Shariff Kabungsuan, a Muslim missionary who spread the Islamic faith in the 14th century Mindanao. <br/><br/>\r\n\r\n During Kudarat\'s rule, Spanish efforts to conquer his sultanate failed, as well as Mindanao\'s conversion to Christianity.', 'May more Muslims turn out to be genuine national heroes, not just of their faith.', 'Learn to do right; seek justice. Defend the oppressed. Take up the cause of the fatherless; plead the case of the widow. <br/>\r\n–<b>Isaiah 1:17</b>', '<i>In human history, we can see sparkles of God\'s redeeming stories</i><br/>\r\n- Pastor Jose Tacadena', 'https://bit.ly/35q85GF', 1, NULL, 'To a great extent, heroism involves seeking justice for one\'s people and defending the oppressed.'),
(84, '2021-01-14', '2021-01-14', 'On The Birth Of Albert Schweitzer, The Nobel-Prize Winning Physician', 'In 1875, Albert Schweitzer, the Nobel Prize-winning physician, was born in France ( part of Germany before ). <br/><br/>\r\n\r\n After finishing theology and philosophy at the universities of Strasbourg, Paris and Berlin, he worked as a pastor and received his M.D in 1913. <br/><br/>\r\n\r\n He and his wife moved to French Equatorial Africa where he founded a hospital in Lambarene ( Gabon now ). <br/><br/>\r\n\r\n After being awarded $33, 000 for being a Nobel Peace Prize winner for 1952, he started and maintained a leprosarium, wrote books, and spoke around the world on valuing life.\r\n', 'May the Nobel Prize linger and expand. May more professionals have a life-long goal of blessing the people and community especially the marginalized poor.', 'Whoever oppresses the poor shows contempt for their Maker, but whoever is kind to the needy honors God. <br/>\r\n- <b>Proverbs 14:31</b>', '<i>In human history, we can see sparkles of God\'s redeeming stories</i><br/>\r\n- Pastor Jose Tacadena', 'https://bit.ly/3nqJVSR', 0, NULL, 'God Himself is honored as we support the poor among us.'),
(85, '2021-01-14', '2021-01-14', 'On The Birth Of Carlos Romulo, The First Filipino To Become President Of The United Nations Gen. Assembly', 'In 1898, Gen. Carlos Romulo, the first Filipino to become president of the United Nations General Assembly, was born. <br/><br/>\r\n\r\n He became UNGA president for its fourth session from 1949 to 1950. <br/><br/>\r\n\r\n He was a reporter at 16, a newspaper editor at 20, and a publisher at 32. He\'s a National Artist Awardee for Literature in 1982. He even won the Pulitzer Prize for Peace in his pre-war evaluations of the military situations in the Pacific area. <br/><br/>\r\n\r\n He was also a co-founder of the Boy Scouts of the Philippines, a general in the US and Phil Army and president of the University of the Philippines. A multi-talented Filipino indeed.', 'May more Filipinos excel in the international scene. May multi-talented people maximize their ability to bless others and honor God.', 'You yourselves know that these hands of mine have supplied my own needs and the needs of my companions. 35 In everything I did, I showed you that by this kind of hard work we must help the weak, remembering the words the Lord Jesus himself said: <i>"It is more blessed to give than to receive.". </i><br/>\r\n–<b>Acts 20:34-35<br/>', '<i>In human history, we can see sparkles of God\'s redeeming stories</i><br/>\r\n- Pastor Jose Tacadena', 'https://bit.ly/3boY3tt', 1, NULL, 'St. Paul, who himself was multi-talented and gifted, demonstrated being hardworking not only to be self-sufficient, but also to bless others.'),
(86, '2021-01-15', '2021-01-15', 'On The Birth Of Martin Luther King Jr.', 'In 1929, Martin Luther King Jr., the American Baptist minister, who was the prominent leader in the Civil rights movement from 1954 to 1968, was born in Atlanta, Georgia. <br/><br/>\r\n\r\n His Christian faith and the influence of Mohandas Gandhi moved him to advocate a non-violent resistance and civil disobedience to segregation (separation of white and black Americans) in the south. <br/><br/>\r\n\r\n In 1955, he co-organized the triumphant Montgomery Bus Boycott, the first major protest of the African-American civil rights movement. <br/><br/>\r\n\r\n In 1963, he gave his world famous line <i>"I Have A Dream" </i> speech before 250, 000 people at the Lincoln Memorial during the March on Washington. In 1964, he became the youngest winner of the Nobel Peace Prize but was assassinated in 1968.\r\n', 'May many more like Martin Luther King Jr. arise from among the people and lead non-violent civil rights movements in their country. May people who lead peaceful campaigns for the betterment of societies be protected from assassination attempts.', 'Speak up for those who cannot speak for themselves, for the rights of all who are destitute.9 Speak up and judge fairly; defend the rights of the poor and needy. <br/>\r\n- <b>Proverbs 31:8-9</b>', '<i>In human history, we can see sparkles of God\'s redeeming stories</i><br/>\r\n- Pastor Jose Tacadena', 'https://bit.ly/2LyGjku', 0, NULL, 'Do you know that we are actually commanded by God to speak and defend the rights of the needy?'),
(87, '2021-01-15', '2021-01-15', 'On The Execution Of Chinese Drug Trafficker Lim Seng', 'In 1973, convicted Chinese drug trafficker Lim Seng was executed by musketry. <br/><br/>\r\n\r\n He was sentenced to death by a military commission during Martial Law as some P3 million worth of heroin was seized from his nine laboratories in Caloocan and other parts in Manila. <br/><br/>\r\n\r\n High-powered firearms were also seized from Seng who was allegedly responsible for proliferation of high-grade heroin in Thailand, Singapore and the Philippines. His execution was said to have stopped even for a while, the drug problem in the country, which the Philippine Constabulary stated, affected 350, 000 people during that time.', 'May real drug lords and pushers be immediately arrested and punished according to law, especially the big-time foreigners. May drug dependents be rehabilitated. May non-addicts be prevented from being hooked on drugs.', 'Woe to those who rise early in the morning to run after their drinks, who stay up late at night till they are inflamed with wine. They have harps and lyres at their banquets, pipes and timbrels and wine, but they have no regard for the deeds of the Lord, no respect for the work of his hands". <br/>\r\n–<b>Isaiah 5:11-12<br/>', '<i>In human history, we can see sparkles of God\'s redeeming stories</i><br/>\r\n- Pastor Jose Tacadena', 'https://bit.ly/3oxZSI5', 1, NULL, ' Being dependent on illegal drugs is worse than wine addiction. They both destroy character and life.'),
(88, '2021-01-16', '2021-01-16', 'On The Prohibition Of Intoxicating Liquors Becoming An American Law.', 'In 1919, the American prohibition of intoxicating liquors, became a law. <br/><br/>\r\n\r\n This 18th Amendment to the US Constitution specifically outlawed the manufacture, sale or transportation of intoxication liquors for beverage purposes. <br/><br/>\r\n\r\n This was after studies about the adverse effects on drinking and the formation of numerous temperance societies spread throughout the USA in the early 19th century. <br/><br/>\r\n\r\n In 1933, the Prohibition was repelled as it failed to stop wine addiction among the Americans and even led to the formation of gangs selling wine.\r\n', 'May the campaign against drinking and drunkenness succeed. May the government and concerned Non-Government Organizations be effective in enforcing laws and local government resolutions against it, and in rehabilitating wine-dependents.', 'Wine is a mocker and beer a brawler; whoever is led astray by them is not wise. <br/>\r\n- <b>Proverbs 20:1</b>', '<i>In human history, we can see sparkles of God\'s redeeming stories</i><br/>\r\n- Pastor Jose Tacadena', 'https://bit.ly/38u0AjU ', 0, NULL, 'May we all realize that drinking wine is dangerous eventually; and may we be determined not to be enslaved by it'),
(89, '2021-01-16', '2021-01-16', 'On The Establishment Of The Lung Center Of The Philippines', 'In 1981, Lung Center of the Philippines was established in Quezon City. <br/><br/>\r\n\r\n This was through Presidential Decree No. 1823 signed by Pres. Ferdinand Marcos. Inaugurated on January 23, 1982 as a tertiary level hospital. It provides health care specifically on lung and pulmonary diseases. <br/><br/>\r\n\r\n Razed down by a fire on May 6, 1998, it was reopened on March 1, 1999 with additional hospital features.', 'May the Lung Center of the Philippines continue to improve in every aspect and facet of health public service. May we all take care of our lungs, avoiding habits that threaten it and our over-all health.', ' The Spirit of God has made me; the breath of the Almighty gives me life. <br/>\r\n–<b>Job 33:4<br/><br/>\r\n\r\n Let everything that has breath praise the Lord. Praise the Lord. <br/>\r\n–<b>Job 33:4<br/>', '<i>In human history, we can see sparkles of God\'s redeeming stories</i><br/>\r\n- Pastor Jose Tacadena', 'https://bit.ly/2JYVlzl', 1, NULL, 'It\'s basic knowledge that our lungs take charge of our respiration or breathing. ( It processes the inflow of oxygen into our body and releases harmful carbon dioxide ) Why did God give us lungs and make us breathe?'),
(90, '2021-01-17', '2021-01-17', 'On The Overthrowing Of Hawaii Monarchy By The Americans.', 'In 1893, the Americans overthrew Queen Liliuokalani, ending the Hawaiian monarchy. <br/><br/>\r\n\r\n The Americans, who were mostly sugar planters under Sanford Ballard Dole, then established a new provincial government with the former as president. <br/><br/>\r\n\r\n The revolt was known to John Stevens, US minister to Hawaii, who even requested for 300 US Marines from the US Cruiser Boston to protect American lives then. <br/><br/>\r\n\r\n Native Hawaiians were mostly Polynesians who arrived there in the 6th century. American traders arrived in the early 18th century. This coup contributed to a series of events that finally made Hawaii an annex of the USA in 1900, and its 50th state in 1959.\r\n', 'May Hawaii continue to progress and be an effective state of the US. May foreigners in Hawaii, including Filipinos, contribute to its peace and order, and development.', 'Now to the King eternal, immortal, invisible, the only God, be honor and glory for ever and ever. Amen. <br/>\r\n- <b>1 Timothy 1:17</b>', '<i>In human history, we can see sparkles of God\'s redeeming stories</i><br/>\r\n- Pastor Jose Tacadena', 'https://bit.ly/3scFVsL', 0, NULL, 'While there are still queens and kings today, only God is the worthy King of all.'),
(91, '2021-01-17', '2021-01-17', 'On The Lifting Of Martial Law Throughout The Philippines', 'In 1981, Pres. Ferdinand Marcos lifted Martial Law throughout the Philippines after declaring it on September 21, 1972. <br/><br/>\r\n\r\n This was through President Proclamation No. 2045 which the then president hoped would show the Filipinos and the world that the situation in the Philippines was finally back to normal. <br/><br/>\r\n\r\n When he proclaimed martial law nine years earlier due to what he claimed as a wave of lawlessness and a threat to communism, press freedom and civil rights were curtailed, the Congress and media establishments were closed down and his critics were arrested. Through martial law\'s lifting, Pres. Marcos also wanted to show that the 1973 Constitution was working effectively, as well as his government', 'May the extended Martial Law in Mindanao this year be implemented justly and not abused by those in power. May lawlessness and rebellion be prevented thoroughly.', 'The God of Israel spoke, the Rock of Israel said to me: \'When one rules over people in righteousness, when he rules in the fear of God, 4 he is like the light of morning at sunrise on a cloudless morning, like the brightness after rain that brings grass from the earth.\' <br/>\r\n–<b>2 Samuel 23:3-4<br/>', '<i>In human history, we can see sparkles of God\'s redeeming stories</i><br/>\r\n- Pastor Jose Tacadena', 'https://bit.ly/3nvmoA6', 1, NULL, 'May our leaders refrain from abusing their authority to prolong their tenure. May they, like King David, rule with righteousness and fear of God'),
(92, '2021-01-18', '2021-01-18', 'On Beginning Of The Post World War I Peace Conference In Paris, France.', 'In 1919, the post-World War I Peace Conference began in Paris, France. <br/><br/>\r\n\r\n This conference lasted six months, was led by the heads of the triumphant Allied Forces – France, Great Britain, the United States and Italy. <br/><br/>\r\n\r\n After much arguments, they required Germany, the main proponent of the losing powers, to forfeit huge territory, pay reparations, and the accept sole blame for the war. <br/><br/>\r\n\r\n While the Allied Forces moved on after this with the establishment of the League of Nations, German\'s anger and resentment with their punishment grew through the years.\r\n', 'May powerful nations refrain from manipulating weaker ones. May abusive countries be thoroughly restrained by the United Nations and/or regional alliances of countries.', '21For then there will be great distress, unequaled from the beginning of the world until now—and never to be equaled again. <i>\'If those days had not been cut short, no one would survive, but for the sake of the elect those days will be shortened. \'</i><br/>\r\n- <b>1 Timothy 1:17</b>', '<i>In human history, we can see sparkles of God\'s redeeming stories</i><br/>\r\n- Pastor Jose Tacadena', 'https://bit.ly/39ctBjq', 0, NULL, 'May we all strive for peace but at the same time be ready for what the Bible prophesied as the coming of the Great Tribulation Period – where turmoil and fear would seem to reign throughout the world.'),
(93, '2021-01-18', '2021-01-18', 'On The Maiden Issue Of Kalayaan, The Official Newspaper Of The Katipunan', 'In 1896, the maiden issue of Kalayaan, the official newspaper of the Katipunan, was published. <br/><br/>\r\n\r\n This was founded and edited by Emilio Jacinto, the <i>\'Brains of the Katipunan\'</i>. Other writers on its first issue were KKK founding head Andres Bonifacio, Pio Valenzuela and Macario Sakay. <br/><br/>\r\n\r\n Around 1,000 – 2, 000 copies were distributed and contributed to the promotion of the revolutionaries\' goals and its recruitment. However, its second issue was not released because the Spanish authorities learned about the Katipunan and discovered its printing press.', 'May nationalistic and developmental writers and publications continue to flourish and be supported by the government and the people.', 'But whenever anyone turns to the Lord, the veil is taken away. 17 Now the Lord is the Spirit, and where the Spirit of the Lord is, there is freedom. <br/>\r\n–<b>2 Corinthians 3:16-17<br/>', '<i>In human history, we can see sparkles of God\'s redeeming stories</i><br/>\r\n- Pastor Jose Tacadena', 'https://bit.ly/38uVUKT', 1, NULL, 'While writers, publications, organizations and certain programs help in fostering freedom, it is the Spirit of God who is the prime source of genuine liberty.'),
(94, '2021-01-19', '2021-01-19', 'On The Indira Gandhi Becoming The First Lady Prime Minister Of India.', 'In 1966, Indira Gandhi became the prime minister of India. <br/><br/>\r\n\r\n This was after then incumbent Prime Minister Lal Bahadur Shastri died, making her the head of the ruling Congress Party. <br/><br/>\r\n\r\n A daughter of Jahawarlal Nehru, independent Republic of India\'s first prime minister, she became a national political figure in 1955 when she was elected to the executive body of the Congress Party. <br/><br/>\r\n\r\n She won the election narrowly a year later but was reelected overwhelmingly in 1971 to become the undisputed head of India.\r\n', 'May India develop some more and have high regard for its women.', 'There is neither Jew nor Gentile, neither slave nor free, nor is there male and female, for you are all one in Christ Jesus. 29 If you belong to Christ, then you are Abraham\'s seed, and heirs according to the promise. <br/>\r\n- <b>Galatians 3:28-29</b>', '<i>In human history, we can see sparkles of God\'s redeeming stories</i><br/>\r\n- Pastor Jose Tacadena', 'https://bit.ly/3q2SlRW', 0, NULL, 'Even with likes of Indira Gandhi, the world in general still looks down on women. It\'s nice to note that God looks at people fairly.'),
(95, '2021-01-19', '2021-01-19', 'On The Inauguration Of The Zamboanga International Airport And Terminal', 'In 1974, the Zamboanga International Airport and Terminal was inaugurated. <br/><br/>\r\n\r\n This airport was built way back in 1945 as Moret Field, by the American and Philippine Commonwealth troops. At its operational peak, about 300 aircrafts flew from this airfield, most of which were from the Marines. <br/><br/>\r\n\r\n Renovated and expanded during Martial Law, this airport became the Philippine tourism industry\'s second front in the south. It is now the third busiest airport in Mindanao after Francisco Bangoy International Airport in Davao City and Lumpia Airport in Cagayan de Oro City.', 'May our airports ( domestic and international ) be world class not only in terms of facilities and service but also in security.', 'and lays the beams of his upper chambers on their waters. He makes the clouds his chariot and rides on the wings of the wind. 4 He makes winds his messengers, flames of fire his servants. <br/>\r\n–<b>Psalm 104:3-4<br/>', '<i>In human history, we can see sparkles of God\'s redeeming stories</i><br/>\r\n- Pastor Jose Tacadena', 'https://bit.ly/3q7hLhq', 1, NULL, 'Most of us are always fascinated with flying, airplanes, and airports. Do you know that God is described as a somewhat incredible supreme flyer?'),
(96, '2021-01-20', '2021-01-20', 'On The Ending of the Iran Hostage Crisis that Freed 52 US Hostages After 444 Days.', 'In 1981, the 444-day Iran hostage crisis ended, as the 52 US hostages were released. <br/><br/>\r\n\r\n The release of the hostages at the US Embassy in Teheran, Iran occurred minutes after Ronald Raegan was inaugurated as the 40th president of the USA. <br/><br/>\r\n\r\n The hostage crisis began after militant Iranian students seized the US Embassy on Nov. 4, 1979. They were outraged that the US government allowed the ousted Shah of Iran travel to New York for medical treatment. <br/><br/>\r\n\r\n With the support of Ayatollah Khomeini, Iran\'s political and religious leader, the crisis lingered even after Pres. Jimmy Carter\'s intervention. The Iranians only released the hostages after the US freed $8 billion in frozen Iranian assets.\r\n', 'May hostage attempts be discovered and prevented and its perpetrators punished justly.', 'A false witness will not go unpunished, and whoever pours out lies will not go free. <br/>\r\n- <b>Proverbs 19:5</b>', '<i>In human history, we can see sparkles of God\'s redeeming stories</i><br/>\r\n- Pastor Jose Tacadena', 'https://bit.ly/3br5Gj4', 0, NULL, 'Some Christian writers consider people being held hostage by sin. That means that being controlled by sin, until we come to God through the Lord Jesus and be liberated from it.'),
(97, '2021-01-20', '2021-01-20', 'On The Cavite Arsenal Mutiny', 'In 1872, the Cavite Mutiny occurred in Fort San Felipe. <br/><br/>\r\n\r\n It was participated in by around 200 Filipino soldiers and laborer of the Engineering and Artillery Corps They revolted after their salaries were reduced upon the order of Governor-General Rafael de Izquierdo, and were subjected to personal taxes. <br/><br/>\r\n\r\n This unsuccessful mutiny eventually led to the unjust implication, arrest and execution of Filipino priests Mariano Gomez, Jose Burgoz and Jacinto Zamora and other leaders on February 17 that year.', 'May mutinies and rebellions be prevented. May police and or military personnel\'s sentiments, criticisms and complaints about the government and their particular institution be heard and somewhat implemented for the betterment of everyone.', 'Do not spread false reports. Do not help a guilty person by being a malicious witness. <br/>\r\n–<b>Exodus 23:1 <br/><br/>\r\n\r\n A false witness will not go unpunished, and whoever pours out lies will not go free <br/>\r\n- <b>Proverbs 19:5</b>', '<i>In human history, we can see sparkles of God\'s redeeming stories</i><br/>\r\n- Pastor Jose Tacadena', 'https://bit.ly/3scXPvt', 1, NULL, 'That the GomBurZa were innocent of the charges filed by the Spaniards were already known then. May we desist from being false witnesses.'),
(98, '2021-01-21', '2021-01-21', 'On The Death Of Vlademir Lenin, The First Head Of Soviet Union And The Instigator Of The Bolshevik.', 'In 1924, Vladimir Lenin, the first head of the Soviet Union and the instigator of Bolshevik Revolution, died of hemorrhage at the age of 54 years old. <br/><br/>\r\n\r\n In 1903, he organized the Bolsheviks, a militant party of the professional revolutionaries who wanted to overthrow the czarist government and put up a Marxist rule. <br/><br/>\r\n\r\n In 1907, the Bolsheviks, with the help of defected soldiers, seized power in Russia. His government nationalized industry and distributed land; and established the Union of Soviet Socialist Republics (USSR) on December 30, 1922.\r\n', 'May armed rebellions be prevented. May the people who espouse rebellion found peaceful means to vent their anger, bitterness and clamor for righteous change in their society. May those in authority be humble enough and positively responsive to the clamor for change.', 'For to us a child is born, to us a son is given, and the government will be on his shoulders. And he will be called Wonderful Counselor, Mighty God, Everlasting Father, Prince of Peace. <br/>\r\n- <b>Isaiah 9:6</b>', '<i>In human history, we can see sparkles of God\'s redeeming stories</i><br/>\r\n- Pastor Jose Tacadena', 'https://bit.ly/2LCYQMe', 0, NULL, 'What distinguish the Lord Jesus Christ from other changers of people or societies was that He didn\'t use armed rebellion. He knew violence will only beget violence and creating transformation through peaceful means is always the best, being the genuine Prince of Peace.');
INSERT INTO `glimpse` (`id`, `title`, `glimpse_date`, `heading`, `content`, `prayer_focus`, `featured_verse`, `featured_quote`, `image_link`, `type`, `created_at`, `transition`) VALUES
(99, '2021-01-21', '2021-01-21', 'On The Birth Of Leon Ma. Guerrero, The Father Of Botany In The Philippines And The Father Of Philippine Pharmacy.', 'In 1853, Leon Ma.Guerrero, the \'Father of Botany in the Philippines\' was born in Ermita, Manila. <br/><br/>\r\n\r\n In 1918, he authored a study on Medicinal Plants on 174 types of plants with healing elements. He was motivated to do this because there was a lot of unavailable synthetic medicine in his time. <br/><br/>\r\n\r\n He was also appointed as a secretary of industry, agriculture, and commerce of Gen. Emilio Aguinaldo\'s cabinet and a delegate to the Malolos Congress. He died on April 13, 1935.', 'May more botanists and pharmacies arise among the Filipinos to help the country to progress in this area. May all our scientists and researchers be more nationalistic like Leon Ma. Guerrero.', 'Then the angel showed me the river of the water of life, as clear as crystal, flowing from the throne of God and of the Lamb 2 down the middle of the great street of the city. On each side of the river stood the tree of life, bearing twelve crops of fruit, yielding its fruit every month. And the leaves of the tree are for the healing of the nations. <br/>\r\n–<b>Revelation 22:1-2<br/>', '<i>In human history, we can see sparkles of God\'s redeeming stories</i><br/>\r\n- Pastor Jose Tacadena', 'https://bit.ly/3bCDHgv ', 1, NULL, 'It appears from the Bible that God Himself who willed that plants contain elements and substances that causes health and healing.'),
(100, '2021-01-22', '2021-01-22', 'On The Arrest Of Andrei Sakharov, The Soviet Physicist For Criticizing USSR.', 'In 1980, Andre Dmitriyevich Sakharov, the Soviet physicist who helped build the USSR\'s first hydrogen bomb, was arrested in Moscow. <br/><br/>\r\n\r\n This was after he criticized the Soviet military occupation in Afghanistan. He was stripped off of his numeric scientific honors and banished to Gorky. Although hailed for helping the USSR detonate its first hydrogen bomb in 1955, he later regretted for the biological hazards of nuclear testing. He called for the cessation of nuclear tests. <br/><br/>\r\n\r\n He even criticized the arms race and the Soviet political system and called for a \'Democratic Pluralistic Society\'. In 1975, he became the first Soviet to win a Nobel Peace Prize.\r\n', 'May more scientists involved in the testing and development of weapons of mass destructions, or any other experiments that endanger lives and or planet desist from doing so. May Russia be more humanitarian and pro-environment, as well as other nations.', 'Learn to do right; seek justice. Defend the oppressed. Take up the cause of the fatherless; plead the case of the widow. <br/>\r\n- <b>Isaiah 1:17</b>', '<i>In human history, we can see sparkles of God\'s redeeming stories</i><br/>\r\n- Pastor Jose Tacadena', 'https://bit.ly/3ovDz61', 0, NULL, ' The fundamental of ( national ) leadership involves being humane and humanitarian; imposing justice and righteousness.'),
(101, '2021-01-22', '2021-01-22', 'On The Birth Of Robert Mcculloch Dick, Editor And Publisher Of Free Press Magazine.', 'In 1873, Robert Mcculloch Dick, editor and publisher of of Free Press Magazine and the one who coined \'Juan dela Cruz\' to refer to Filipinos, was born in Edinburg, Scotland. <br/><br/>\r\n\r\n He migrated to the US when he was 19 years old and earned a Bachelor of Arts degree in 1899 as a working student. He arrived in Manila in 1900 and become a Manila Times court reporter. He noticed many Filipinos being jailed with the surname \'dela Cruz\' and begun using that \'term\' generically to all Pinoys. <br/><br/>\r\n\r\n He became the owner of the weekly Free Press Magazine after buying it and becoming its editor in 1908. Through this magazine, he helped in the establishment of press freedom in the Philippines.', 'May publishers, editors and writers continue to safeguard their rights and that of their country. May people continue to support press freedom. May everyone, especially writers, always seek and promote the truth.', 'You, my brothers and sisters, were called to be free. But do not use your freedom to indulge the flesh[a]; rather, serve one another humbly in love. <br/>\r\n–<b>Galatians 5:13<br/>', '<i>In human history, we can see sparkles of God\'s redeeming stories</i><br/>\r\n- Pastor Jose Tacadena', 'https://bit.ly/3ovEsvn', 1, NULL, 'Jesus taught us that true freedom comes from knowing the truth, especially His teachings; and that we must not abuse our freedom.'),
(102, '2021-01-23', '2021-01-23', 'On The Elizabeth Blackwell Becoming The First Woman Doctor In The Us History.', 'In 1849, Elizabeth Blackwell became the first woman to be officially recognized as a physician in the US history. <br/><br/>\r\n\r\n That was after the Geneva College in New York granted her medical. A British citizen, she was also the first woman on the Medical Registrar of the Geneva Medical Council in United Kingdom. <br/><br/>\r\n\r\n Blackwell pioneered the promotion of the education of women in medicine, and was recognized also in the US and UK as an effective social and moral reformer. As a tribute to her, an Elizabeth Blackwell medal is awarded every year to one woman who has contributed to the cause of promoting women in medicine.\r\n', 'May more women take medicine and succeed in it. May more like Blackwell rise up who will also promote social and moral reforms while excelling in their chosen professional field.', 'On hearing this, Jesus said, "It is not the healthy who need a doctor, but the sick. <br/>\r\n- <b>Matthew 9:12</b>', '<i>In human history, we can see sparkles of God\'s redeeming stories</i><br/>\r\n- Pastor Jose Tacadena', 'https://bit.ly/3s8R39P', 0, NULL, 'Do you know that Jesus is recognized in the Bible as the total physician not only because He can heal our physical sickness but our spiritual disease as well.'),
(103, '2021-01-23', '2021-01-23', 'On The Inauguration Of The First Philippine Republic', 'In 1899, the first Philippine Republic, more popularly known as the Malolos Republic, was inaugurated in Bulacan. <br/><br/>\r\n\r\n That was seven months after the declaration of Philippine Independence from the Spanish regime. Gen. Emilio Aguinaldo who was president of this Republic, adopted the Constitution drafted by the Philippine Constitutional Convention in Barasoain Church in Malolos in January 17, 1899. <br/><br/>\r\n\r\n However, this republic ended right away with the capture and surrender of Aguinaldo to the American forces on March 23, 1901; and the general\'s alliance to the US on April 1, 1901.', 'May God\'s perfect will prevail on the attempt of some politicians to change our constitution and form of government, and the implementation of the Bangsamoro Organic Law. May our leaders refrain from using their influence to manipulate our laws, constitutions and form of government for their selfish gains.', 'Submit yourselves for the Lord\'s sake to every human authority: whether to the emperor, as the supreme authority, 14 or to governors, who are sent by him to punish those who do wrong and to commend those who do right. 15 For it is God\'s will that by doing good you should silence the ignorant talk of foolish people. <br/>\r\n–<b>1 Peter 2:13-15<br/>', '<i>In human history, we can see sparkles of God\'s redeeming stories</i><br/>\r\n- Pastor Jose Tacadena', 'https://bit.ly/3i0lWIP', 1, NULL, 'Any form of government or constitution that recognize God and His Word may well be alright for its people. The key is to submit the government and be active and righteous citizens.'),
(104, '2021-01-24', '2021-01-24', 'On The First Canned Beer Being Sold In The World.', 'In 1935, the first canned beer in the world went on sale in USA. <br/><br/>\r\n\r\n This was after Gottfried Krueger Brewing Company delivered 2, 000 of its Finest Beer to its customers in Virginia. <br/><br/>\r\n\r\n With 91% of their drinkers approving the canned beer, the said company bolstered their production even more. By the end of 1935, more than 200 million cans had been produced and sold. At present, canned beer accounts for half of the $20 billion US beer industry.\r\n', 'May the government\'s campaign to encourage their drinking people to practice moderation succeed. May the rest of the people find better ways to unwind and relax than to drink wine.', 'Woe to those who are heroes at drinking wine and champions at mixing drinks. <br/>\r\n- <b>Isaiah 5:22</b>', '<i>In human history, we can see sparkles of God\'s redeeming stories</i><br/>\r\n- Pastor Jose Tacadena', 'https://bit.ly/38sbJ4R', 0, NULL, 'The prophet Isaiah has strong words to those who \'specializes\' in drinking wine.'),
(105, '2021-01-24', '2021-01-24', 'On The Surrender Of A Southern Luzon Npa Commander.', 'In 2002, a Southern Tagalog NPA Commander surrendered to the government. <br/><br/>\r\n\r\n Rodante Paminiano, alias \'Ka Choy\', was listed in the Armed Forces of the Philippines, \'Order of the Battle\'. <br/><br/>\r\n\r\n He was part of the Committee of the Guerilla Field Oriental Mindoro and the head of the security force of the New People\'s Army Melito Flor Command. <br/><br/>\r\n\r\n He was said to be responsible for the security during the abduction of Major Noel Buan, and a Philippine Constabulary Colonel years ago. He surrendered to the local authorities with several members of the security force.', 'May more NPA rebels surrender to the government. May the government be effective in rehabilitating and reintegrating rebel returnees.', 'Submit yourselves, then, to God. Resist the devil, and he will flee from you. <br/>\r\n–<b> James 4:7<br/>', '<i>In human history, we can see sparkles of God\'s redeeming stories</i><br/>\r\n- Pastor Jose Tacadena', 'https://bit.ly/35pZjbM', 1, NULL, 'God is the one we all need to surrender our life into, to defeat the fiercest enemy we have - Satan'),
(106, '2021-01-25', '2021-01-25', 'On The Discovery Of The World\'s Largest Diamond In South Africa.', 'In 1905, the world\'s largest diamond was found in South Africa. <br/><br/>\r\n\r\n Called the \'Cullinan\', the 3.106 carat, 1.33-lb diamond was found at the Premier mine in Pretoria, South Africa. <br/><br/>\r\n\r\n It was discovered by Frederick Wells, a mine supervisor, 18-feet below the earth\'s surface and gave it to Sir Thomas Cullinan, the owner of the mine. Cullinan sold it to Transvaal government which gave it as a birthday gift to Britain\'s King Edward VII.\r\n', 'May the search for precious stones worldwide do not endanger the environment and the people tasked to do so.  May the society in general refrain from being engrossed with jewelry.', 'The foundations of the city walls were decorated with every kind of precious stone. The first foundation was jasper, the second sapphire, the third agate, the fourth emerald, 20 the fifth onyx, the sixth ruby, the seventh chrysolite, the eighth beryl, the ninth topaz, the tenth turquoise, the eleventh jacinth, and the twelfth amethyst. 21 The twelve gates were twelve pearls, each gate made of a single pearl. The great street of the city was of gold, as pure as transparent glass. <br/>\r\n- <b>Revelations 21:19-21</b>', '<i>In human history, we can see sparkles of God\'s redeeming stories</i><br/>\r\n- Pastor Jose Tacadena', 'https://bit.ly/2XuApDu', 0, NULL, 'Do you know that the coming New Jerusalem will be literally filled with jewels and precious stones?'),
(107, '2021-01-25', '2021-01-25', 'On The Birth Of Corazon Aquino, The First Woman President Of The Philippines.', 'In 1933, Pres. Corazon Aquino, the first woman president of the Philippines, was born in Paniqui, Tarlac. <br/><br/>\r\n\r\n Best remembered for leading the 1986 EDSA People Power Revolution which overthrew the authoritarian regime of Pres. Ferdinand Marcos, she was the 11th Head of the State of the Philippines. <br/><br/>\r\n\r\n That was after being sworn on Feb. 25, 1986 for winning the snap election she joined in the name of her assassinated husband – Sen. Ninoy and because of the clamor of millions of Filipinos. <br/><br/>\r\n\r\n She finished her term in 1992 and returned to private life. TIME Magazine honored her as the \'Saint of Democracy\'.', 'May more women leaders be recognized in the society. May we manifest genuine concern and skills for the welfare of the nation and people.', 'Blessed are those who act justly, who always do what is right. <br/>\r\n–<b> Psalm 106:3<br/>', '<i>In human history, we can see sparkles of God\'s redeeming stories</i><br/>\r\n- Pastor Jose Tacadena', 'https://bit.ly/3oxs123', 1, NULL, 'May we all strive to live justly, righteously and peacefully with others'),
(108, '2021-01-26', '2021-01-26', 'On The Founding Of Australia.', 'In 1788, Australia was founded by British Captain Arthur Phillip. This was after his fleet of 11 British ships carrying more than 700 convicts and 300 marines and other officers discovered Australia ( New South Wales then ) after eight months of voyage. <br/><br/>\r\n\r\n Commissioned by Britain to establish an agricultural work camp there for British convicts, Phillip appointed prisoners to responsibility and oversight positions. In 1808, the migrants begun observing the January 26 as their foundation day. In 1818, the said date became the official \'Australia day\'.\r\n', 'May Australia continue to progress and assist third world countries develop. May prisoners be given sufficient opportunities to be rehabilitated and re-integrated to their society.', 'he does not treat us as our sins deserve or repay us according to our iniquities. 11 For as high as the heavens are above the earth, so great is his love for those who fear him; 12 as far as the east is from the west, so far has he removed our transgressions from us. <br/>\r\n- <b>Psalm 103:10-12</b>', '<i>In human history, we can see sparkles of God\'s redeeming stories</i><br/>\r\n- Pastor Jose Tacadena', 'https://bit.ly/35sJPUG', 0, NULL, 'That the now mighty and respected Australia was founded and developed by mostly convicted prisoners should encourage all of us about the power of hope, forgiveness, new beginnings and perseverance based on God\'s love.'),
(109, '2021-01-26', '2021-01-26', 'On The Prohibition Of Slaughtering Carabaos.', 'In 1954, Pres. Ramon Magsaysay prohibited the slaughtering of carabaos. <br/><br/>\r\n\r\n This was through Executive Order No. 8 which took effect on January 31, 1954. <br/><br/>\r\n\r\n He was informed by then Director of Animal Industry Manuel Sumulong, that in the previous year alone, 82, 401 carabaos were slaughtered in Manila and suburbs and provinces. <br/><br/>\r\n\r\n This indiscriminate killing had resulted in a scarcity of these animals and a rise on the price of carabaos so that poor farmers couldn\'t afford to buy animals for their farm work.', 'May our carabaos and other agricultural animals be well taken care of and live longer lives. May Christians be proactive in taking care of their pets and in challenging other pet owners to do the same.', 'He provides food for the cattle and for the young ravens when they call. <br/>\r\n–<b> Psalm 147:9<br/>', '<i>In human history, we can see sparkles of God\'s redeeming stories</i><br/>\r\n- Pastor Jose Tacadena', 'https://bit.ly/38wPFpW', 1, NULL, 'Do you know that God Himself cares for animals? And righteous people ought to take good care of their animals.'),
(110, '2021-01-27', '2021-01-27', 'On The Founding Of National Geographic Society.', 'In 1888, the National Geographic Society was founded in Washington, DC. <br/><br/>\r\n\r\n This was after 33 geographers, explorers, researchers, lawyers, cartographers, military officers and financers met, drafted a constitution and elected Gardiner Greene Hubbard, lawyer and philanthropist to become its president. <br/><br/>\r\n\r\n Nine months later, the society published its first issue of National Geographic magazine which now sells nine million copies monthly. Today, the NGS sponsors expeditions and research projects about natural phenomena; and is vital in numerous achievements in exploration and science.\r\n', 'May the NGS and other scientific groups continue to succeed in giving humanity better understanding and stewardship of our physical world and universe. May our understanding of science bring us to greater appreciation of our Maker.', 'He sits enthroned above the circle of the earth, and its people are like grasshoppers. He stretches out the heavens like a canopy, and spreads them out like a tent to live in. <br/>\r\n- <b>Isaiah 40:22</b>', '<i>In human history, we can see sparkles of God\'s redeeming stories</i><br/>\r\n- Pastor Jose Tacadena', 'https://bit.ly/3q9lPxG', 0, NULL, 'There are actually a number of verses in the Bible that may well be considered glimpses of scientific information. The end-line is that we recognize God is the creator of nature.'),
(111, '2021-01-27', '2021-01-27', 'On The Birth Of Juan Crisostomo Soto, The Father Of Pampanga Literature.', 'In 1867, Juan Crisostomo Soto, the \'Father of Pampanga Literature\' was born in Sta. Ines, Bacolor, Pampanga. <br/><br/>\r\n\r\n He has written numerous lyrical poems, historical dramas, comic plays and sarswelas ( plays with songs and dances ) as Crissot. <br/><br/>\r\n\r\n The journalist translated a number of Spanish literature into Pampango, promoted Pampango ideals with the help of Maximo Hizon and contributed to the \'La Independencia\' the revolutionary paper. <br/><br/>\r\n\r\n He also joined the Katipunan in fighting the Spaniards.', 'May more Filipino journalists, publishers and artists highlight local dialects and culture. May they remain nationalistic while exploring and expressing their talents.', 'Let the message of Christ dwell among you richly as you teach and admonish one another with all wisdom through psalms, hymns, and songs from the Spirit, singing to God with gratitude in your hearts. <br/>\r\n–<b> Colossians 3:16<br/>', '<i>In human history, we can see sparkles of God\'s redeeming stories</i><br/>\r\n- Pastor Jose Tacadena', 'https://bit.ly/2K1n9TK', 1, NULL, 'Both literature and music are powerful tools in communicating our ideals and messages. Even God wants these to be used as tools of Christian education and worship.'),
(112, '2021-01-28', '2021-01-28', 'On The Space Shuttle Challenger\'s Mid-Air Explosion.', 'In 1986, the space shuttle Challenger exploded in mid-air, just 70 seconds after lift-off, killing all of its six astronauts and a guest teacher passenger. The crash happened above the Cape Canaveral in Florida, USA; in full view of millions of television spectators. The investigating team tasked by then US Pres. Ronald Reagan discovered that the explosion was triggered by the malfunctioning of the elastic \'O-Ring\' seal in one of the two solid-fuel rockets. <br/><br/>\r\n\r\n After two years of space inactivity and redesigning a number of space shuttle features, the National Aeronautics and Space Administration resumed shuttle flights with the triumphant launching of the Discovery in September,  1988.\r\n', 'May there be no more space exploration tragedy. May our scientists develop more technology to safeguard projects, equipment and people involved in space studies and explorations.', 'When I consider your heavens, the work of your fingers, the moon and the stars, which you have set in place, 4 what is mankind that you are mindful of them, human beings that you care for them? <br/>\r\n- <b>Psalm 8:3-4</b>', '<i>In human history, we can see sparkles of God\'s redeeming stories</i><br/>\r\n- Pastor Jose Tacadena', 'https://bit.ly/2LImtU0', 0, NULL, 'As we continue to see the universe and the fascinating creation atop us, may we reflect on what King David realized while meditating upon them. That God values us more than these.'),
(113, '2021-01-28', '2021-01-28', 'On The Birth Of Julian Felipe, Composer Of Lupang Hinirang.', 'In 1861, Julian Felipe, composer of Lupang Hinirang – the Philippine National Anthem, was born in Cavite City, Cavite. <br/><br/>\r\n\r\n He became the organist in St. Peter\'s Parish Church at an early age, motivating him to compose songs also. <br/><br/>\r\n\r\n When the Revolution occurred in 1896, he joined the fight against the Spaniards and was jailed. After being released, he rejoined Gen. Aguinaldo\'s troops. <br/><br/>\r\n\r\n He was asked to compose \'Marcha Nacional Filipinas\' which was played as the Philippine flag was hoisted on June 12, 1898. This was adopted later as our national anthem, with the lyrics coming from Jose Palma.', 'May we continue to respect the message of our national anthem. May God\'s perfect will be done in Sen. Tito Sotto\'s proposal to change the last line of this song ( which was defeatist ) and in Sen. Dick Gordon\'s bill seeking one more ray to the sun in the flag ( to recognize the Muslim leaders ).', 'Then Moses and the Israelites sang this song to the Lord: <i>/"I will sing to the Lord, for he is highly exalted. Both horse and driver he has hurled into the sea. 2 The Lord is my strength and my defense; he has become my salvation. He is my God, and I will praise him, my father\'s God, and I will exalt him. 3 The Lord is a warrior; the Lord is his name.\'</i><br/>\r\n–<b> Exodus 15:1-3<br/>', '<i>In human history, we can see sparkles of God\'s redeeming stories</i><br/>\r\n- Pastor Jose Tacadena', 'https://bit.ly/3i27UXt', 1, NULL, 'Do you know that the earliest composition in the Bible that sort of served as the Jewish anthem and praise to God was about their victory over the pursuing Egyptian soldiers?'),
(114, '2021-01-29', '2021-01-29', 'On China\'s Deng And US\' Carter Signing Peace Accords.', 'In 1979, China\'s Deng Xiaoping and USA\'s Jimmy Carter signed a peace accords. <br/><br/>\r\n\r\n This finally stopped the decades of opposition between the US and the People\'s Republic of China. Xiaoping played them more crucial role in this by leading China to a major transformation from its rigid orthodox communist beliefs. He rallied for individualism and material incentives in China\'s attempt for economic modernization. <br/><br/>\r\n\r\n So Deng opened China to foreign investment and created closer ties with the West. Eventually, the US granted full diplomatic recognition to China.\r\n', 'May the US and China develop genuine relationship with each other even with their stiff competition in economy and forging alliances with other countries.', '"Anyone who withholds kindness from a friend forsakes the fear of the Almighty\' <br/>\r\n- <b>Job 6:14</b>', '<i>In human history, we can see sparkles of God\'s redeeming stories</i><br/>\r\n- Pastor Jose Tacadena', 'https://bit.ly/38tj8Rw', 0, NULL, 'We all need to learn to adjust and befriend others in order to be better individuals and groups… that means being kind and recognizing kindness from our friends.'),
(115, '2021-01-29', '2021-01-29', 'On The Birth Of Francisco Santiago, The Father Of Kundiman.', 'In 1889, Francisco Santiago – the \'Father of Kundiman\' was born in Santa Maria, Bulacan. <br/><br/>\r\n\r\n He became piano instructor at 27 years old at the University of the Philippines Conservatory of Music. <br/><br/>\r\n\r\n He made numerous compositions and his most famous piece \'Kundiman\' was sung in 1917 before the Royal Court of Spain upon the request of King Alfonso XIII. <br/><br/>\r\n\r\n He got his doctorate degree in 1924 at the Chicago Music School and became a director of the UP Conservatory of Music before being named UP Emeritus Professor of Piano on May 25, 1946.', 'May the younger generation appreciate our classical love songs. May our composers, writers and artists refrain from making romantic artworks that promote pre-marital and extra marital sex, and plain lustful actions.', 'Dear children, let us not love with words or speech but with actions and in truth <br/>\r\n–<b> 1 John 3:18<br/>', '<i>In human history, we can see sparkles of God\'s redeeming stories</i><br/>\r\n- Pastor Jose Tacadena', 'https://bit.ly/35rQDBV', 1, NULL, 'While most love songs titillate us and give us goosebumps, it is eventually by actions, not by just feel-good songs that we prove our love.'),
(116, '2021-01-30', '2021-01-30', 'On The Assassination Of Mohandas Karamchand Gandhi.', 'In 1948, Mohandas Karamchand Gandhi, Indian Independence Movement\'s political and spiritual leader, was assassinated in New Delhi. <br/><br/>\r\n\r\n Also called \'Mahatma\' for being \'high-souled\' and \'venerable\', he\'s given an opportunity to study law in England in 1888 when he was just 19 years old. In 1893, he went to South Africa for work. <br/><br/>\r\n\r\n It was in South Africa when he began fighting injustice and defending his countrymen\'s rights through non-violent means. He organized the Indian National Congress that pressured the British government to allow more liberty to the Indians and eventually give them national freedom.  <br/><br/>\r\n\r\n He was killed by a Hindu extremist who objected his tolerance for the Muslims.\r\n', 'May India continue to progress while expanding the liberty of their people. May the ideals sacrifice and challenges of Gandhi be replicated.', 'Do nothing out of selfish ambition or vain conceit. Rather, in humility value others above yourselves, 4 not looking to your own interests but each of you to the interests of the others. <br/>\r\n- <b>Philippians 2:3-4</b>', '<i>In human history, we can see sparkles of God\'s redeeming stories</i><br/>\r\n- Pastor Jose Tacadena', 'https://bit.ly/2K6TpVI', 0, NULL, 'We may not be able to replicate exactly what Gandhi did for his countrymen, but can follow St. Paul\'s God-given command to look for the welfare of others.'),
(117, '2021-01-30', '2021-01-30', 'On The Establishment Of The Philippine Supreme Court By Gov. Gen. Elwell Otis.', 'In 1899, the Supreme Court was organized in Manila by US Gen Elwell Stephen Otis. <br/><br/>\r\n\r\n Superseding the Spanish Audencia, it was composed of six Filipino and three American justices. It was presided by Don Cayetano Arellano, with Don Manuel Araullo as chairman of the Civil Branch and Don Reymundo Milleza as Chairman of the Criminal Branch. <br/><br/>\r\n\r\n Except the three Americans, all of them served as judges during the Spanish regime. <br/><br/>\r\n\r\n Under this court, the defendant was fully informed of the accusations against him, has the right to appear and defend himself and post bail, which were all not allowed before.', 'May our Supreme Court be composed of truly God-fearing men and women who are qualified in all fronts to such lofty position. May this court remain independent from the executive and legislative branches of the government, and make just decisions always.', 'If any of you has a dispute with another, do you dare to take it before the ungodly for judgment instead of before the Lord\'s people? 2 Or do you not know that the Lord\'s people will judge the world? And if you are to judge the world, are you not competent to judge trivial cases? Therefore, if you have disputes about such matters, do you ask for a ruling from those whose way of life is scorned in the church? 5 I say this to shame you. Is it possible that there is nobody among you wise enough to judge a dispute between believers? <br/>\r\n–<b> 1 Corinthians 6:1-3, 4-5<br/>', '<i>In human history, we can see sparkles of God\'s redeeming stories</i><br/>\r\n- Pastor Jose Tacadena', 'https://bit.ly/3bqGpp2', 1, NULL, 'While the secular courts have great values to societies, do you know that Christians were discouraged by St. Paul to file cases against each other on such institution? He prefers that Christians settle disputes among themselves.'),
(118, '2021-01-31', '2021-01-31', 'On US Pres. Harry Truman Approving The Development Of The Hydrogen Bomb.', 'In 1950, US Pres. Harry Truman announced approval to the development of the hydrogen bomb. <br/><br/>\r\n\r\n This approval meant that the US government would give total support and funding for the world\'s first \'superbomb\'. <br/><br/>\r\n\r\n On November 1962, the US donated successfully \'Mike\' on the Elugelab Atoll in the Pacific Marshall Islands. .  <br/><br/>\r\n\r\n The 10.4 megaton thermonuclear device quickly vaporized an entire island and left behind a crater more than one mile wide. A superbomb indeed.\r\n', 'May the development of such bombs and other weapons of mass destruction be prevented. May all the stored nuclear bombs around the world be strictly guarded and deactivated, if possible.', 'But the day of the Lord will come like a thief. The heavens will disappear with a roar; the elements will be destroyed by fire, and the earth and everything done in it will be laid bare.11 Since everything will be destroyed in this way, what kind of people ought you to be? You ought to live holy and godly lives. <br/>\r\n- <b>2 Peter 3:10-11</b>', '<i>In human history, we can see sparkles of God\'s redeeming stories</i><br/>\r\n- Pastor Jose Tacadena', 'https://bit.ly/3qaOr9U', 0, NULL, 'Still, the Bible prophecy scholars believe that some of these bombs may be used to destroy the Earth in due time.'),
(119, '2021-01-31', '2021-01-31', 'On Dr. Maria Paz Mendoza Guanzon Becoming The First Female Member Of The Board Of Regents The University Of The Philippines.', 'In 1946, Maria Paz Mendoza Guanzon became the first female member of the Board of Regents of the University of the Philippines. <br/><br/>\r\n\r\n Born in Pandacan, Manila, this pathologist, professor, writer and social reformer, was 62 years old. <br/><br/>\r\n\r\n By that time, she already was the first Filipino woman to acquire a high school diploma and the first woman to receive a medical degree from UP ( in 1912 ). <br/><br/>\r\n\r\n She founded the Philippines Association for University of Women and the president of the Liga Nacional de Damas Filipinas which was dedicated to the national independence of the Philippines and the right to suffrage of women.', 'May more women succeed in medicine and other male-dominated professions. May our society continue to expand its recognition of women.', 'Nevertheless, in the Lord woman is not independent of man, nor is man independent of woman. 12 For as woman came from man, so also man is born of woman. But everything comes from God. <br/>\r\n–<b> 1 Corinthians 11:11-12<br/>', '<i>In human history, we can see sparkles of God\'s redeeming stories</i><br/>\r\n- Pastor Jose Tacadena', ' https://bit.ly/2LIC8Ti ', 1, NULL, 'It is good to be reminded that as far as our Maker is concerned, both men and women are important; and must accept each other as partners.');
INSERT INTO `glimpse` (`id`, `title`, `glimpse_date`, `heading`, `content`, `prayer_focus`, `featured_verse`, `featured_quote`, `image_link`, `type`, `created_at`, `transition`) VALUES
(120, '2021-02-01', '2021-02-01', 'On The Publishing of The First Portion of Oxford Dictionary', 'In 1884, the first portion of the Oxford English dictionary. The most comprehensive and accurate of the English language was published.<br/><br/>\r\n\r\n The book was conceptualized in 1857 by the members of London\'s Philological Society, and was finished through its 125 portions only in 1928. It covers more than half a million words with its historical and etymological background, pronunciation guide and cross references. <br/><br/>\r\n\r\n The OED has now supplement that publish every year new entries from across the globe. It has also an electronic version.\r\n', 'May the English language continue to be vibrant and expand using cross references from other languages. May we develop the desire and skill to learn many languages.', 'Undoubtedly there are all sorts of language in the world, yet none of them is without meaning. <br/>\r\n- <b>1 Corinthians 14:10</b>', '<i>In human history, we can see sparkles of God\'s redeeming stories</i><br/>\r\n- Pastor Jose Tacadena','https://bit.ly/2XTD3mA', 0, NULL, 'While we should appreciate the distinctiveness of the languages of other people, we must strive to make our own speech more than the line with God\'s standards. We must strive to speak only thongs and messages that lift up others and glorify God.'),
(121, '2021-02-01', '2021-02-01', 'On The Official Declaration of Narra As The Philippine National Tree', 'In 1934, Narra was officially declared as Philippine National Tree by US Governor General Frank Murphy. <br/><br/>\r\n\r\n This was through the Executive Proclamation No. 652. Having the scientific name Pterocarpus, the strong and durable Narra aptly symbolizes the Filipinos\' sturdiness and strength of character.', 'May the Narra trees in the country be preserved. May all the national symbols of Philippines be promoted regularly and their challenges applied by Filipinos.', 'Blessed is the one who does not walk-in step with wicked or stand in the way that sinners take or sit in the company of mockers, 2 but whose delight is in the law of the Lord, and who meditates on His law, day and night. 3 That person is like a tree planted by streams of water, which yields its fruit in season and whose leaf does not wither whatever they do prospers.<br/>\r\n–<b>Psalms 1:1-3</b>', '<i>In human history, we can see sparkles of God\'s redeeming stories</i><br/>\r\n- Pastor Jose Tacadena', 'https://bit.ly/38W3AG3', 1, NULL, 'Even the Bible compares people to fruit-bearing trees. Our character is determined by the kind of fruits we bear. (Matthew 7:17-20) So how do we bear good fruit? We must strive to bear good fruits by obeying God\'s Word.'),
(122, '2021-02-02', '2021-02-02', 'On The Ending Of The Nine-Year Russian Military Occupation in Afghanistan', 'In 1989, the nine-year military occupation of Afghanistan by the Russian ended.<br/><br/>\r\n\r\n This was after the final column of the 120,000 strong Red Army forces left Kabul, the nation\'s capital. <br/><br/>\r\n\r\n Historians believe that the Russian troops\' return to their country was indicative of the surprising victory of the US-backed but totally inferior Afghan Mujahideen guerillas.\r\n', 'The Afghanistan fully achieved its independence and progress as a nation recognized by the world. May it refrain from being used for terrorism.', 'Then my enemies will turn back when I call for help. By this I will know that God is for me. <br/>\r\n- <b>Psalm 56:9</b>', '<i>In human history, we can see sparkles of God\'s redeeming stories</i><br/>\r\n- Pastor Jose Tacadena','https://bit.ly/3isnvzO', 0, NULL, 'The Afghans victory against the invading Russian is another testament that underdogs can upset bigger enemies especially if they are united, preserving and trusting in God. We must strive to seek God\'s help always to ensure victory over life\'s trials.'),
(123, '2021-02-02', '2021-02-02', 'On The Establishment of National\'s Citizen\'s Army, the forerunner of The Armed Forces of the Philippines.', 'In 1899, the National Citizen\'s army, the forerunner of the armed forces of the Philippines, was established under the Malolos Republic. <br/><br/>\r\n\r\n Prior to that, the Filipinos had the revolutionary forces against the Spanish colonial government beginning in August 30, 1896. Then the Philippine Army was founded after the revolutionary government under the 1897 Tejeros Convention was formed. Captain General Artemio Ricarte led this group. <br/><br/>\r\n\r\n The National Citizen\'s Army fought the Americans during the US-Philippine War from February 4, 1899 to September 25, 1903 when the last Filipino general, Gen. Simeon Ola surrendered to the Americans.', 'May the Armed Force of the Philippines continue to develop in personnel character and qualifications, as well as in logistics and equipment. May it insurgents and rebels without suffering casualty.', 'Therefore, put on the full armor of God, so that when the day of evil comes, you may be able to stand your ground, and after you have done everything, to stand 14 stand firm then, with the belt of truth buckled around your waist, with breastplate of righteousness in place, 15 and with your feet fitted with the readiness that comes from the Gospel of peace. 16 In addition to all of this, take up the shield of faith, with which you can extinguished all the flaming arrows of the evil one. 17 Take the helmet of salvation and the sword of Spirit, which is the sword of God.<br/>\r\n–<b>Ephesians 6:13-17</b>', '<i>In human history, we can see sparkles of God\'s redeeming stories</i><br/>\r\n- Pastor Jose Tacadena', 'https://bit.ly/3nWKLH8', 1, NULL, 'The Christian, who is a soldier against Satan and his demons, need to be in full uniform to win always. We must strive to wear the Christian armor through the Holy Spirit\'s power.');
INSERT INTO `glimpse` (`id`, `title`, `glimpse_date`, `heading`, `content`, `prayer_focus`, `featured_verse`, `featured_quote`, `image_link`, `type`, `created_at`, `transition`) VALUES
(124, '2021-02-03', '2021-02-03', 'On The Ending Of US Trade Embargo Against Vietnam.', 'In 1994, US Pres. Bill Clinton ordered the end of the trade embargo against Vietnam.<br/><br/>\r\n\r\n This was after nineteen years of that embargo against the communist government that toppled their allied democratic Saigon (or South Vietnam). <br/><br/>\r\n\r\n The reason for the end of embargo was because the communist government which the US fought for years, finally helped them find the 2,238 American "missing in action" soldiers. In July, a year later, US eventually established full diplomatic relations with Vietnam with Pres. Clinton becoming the first president to visit that country in 2000 since 1969 when Pres. Richard Nixon visited South Vietnam.\r\n', 'May Vietnam and the US continue to develop its relationship that benefit them both. May Vietnam continue to progress but at the same time desist from persecuting its Christian citizens and missionaries there.', 'Let us therefore make any effort to do what leads to peace and to mutual edification. <br/>\r\n- <b>Romans 14:19 </b>', '<i>In human history, we can see sparkles of God\'s redeeming stories</i><br/>\r\n- Pastor Jose Tacadena','https://bit.ly/38U4faX', 0, NULL, 'Trade relations teach us about respecting and blessing each other. As Christians, we are more accountable for the application of the principle. We must strive to foster better agreement and partnership with others.'),
(125, '2021-02-03', '2021-02-03', 'On The Introduction of The Concept of Insurance Company in The Philippines.', 'In 1827, the concept of the insurance company was introduced in the Philippines. <br/><br/>\r\n\r\n This was when Lloyd\'s of London appointed Strachman, Murray & Company, Inc. at its representative here during the Spanish regime. <br/><br/>\r\n\r\n It eventually led to the introduction of life insurance in Canada in the local insurance market 1898. The first totally Filipino life insurance company here was the Insular Life Assurance Co. Ltd. which was established in 1910.', 'May the insurance life industry in the country flourish, with its owners and personnel refraining from any sort of scam that victimizes the people.', 'How can we insure it? By entrusting our life to the Lord Jesus and live for God. <i>"I give the eternal life, and they shall never perish: no one will snatch them out of my hand."\ </i><br/>\r\n–<b>John 10:28</b>', '<i>In human history, we can see sparkles of God\'s redeeming stories</i><br/>\r\n- Pastor Jose Tacadena', 'https://bit.ly/2KqEOEz', 1, NULL, 'It comforts in the sense that even if we die, we need not burden our loved ones with the expensive and hard task of taking care of burial ang everything related to it. May the people realize that it is more important to secure our spiritual life than the physical. We must strive to entrust our lives to God to be secured for eternity.'),
(126, '2021-02-04', '2021-02-04', 'On George Washington Being Elected As The First President of The United States.', 'In 1789, George Washington was elected as the first president of the United States.<br/><br/>\r\n\r\n . He was unanimously elected by all 69 presidential electors who represented 10 of the 11 states that raffled the US Constitution. He was the commander of the "Patriots", during the Revolutionary War (1775-1783) which gained their Independence from Britain. <br/><br/>\r\n\r\n He also presided the Constitutional Convention in 1787, that established the federal form of government of the US. He was eventually honored as the "Father of the USA"\.\r\n', 'May the US preserve its reputation as the land o the brave and the free, as a baston of democracy, and as a God-fearing nation as its funders strived or. May our coming election become much better in integrity, honesty and swiftness of process and result.', 'Kings detest wrongdoing for a throne is established through righteousness. <br/>\r\n- <b>Proverbs 16:12 </b>', '<i>In human history, we can see sparkles of God\'s redeeming stories</i><br/>\r\n- Pastor Jose Tacadena','https://bit.ly/2M7htbp', 0, NULL, 'May our national leaders hate evil and lead well. After all, that\'s how King Solomon described (through the Holy Spirit\'s inspiration) true kings. We must strive to support righteous leaders and goodness.'),
(127, '2021-02-04', '2021-02-04', 'On The Beginning of The Philippine-American War.', 'In 1899, the Philippine-American war begun. <br/><br/>\r\n\r\n In 1899, the Philippine-American war begun. <br/><br/>\r\n\r\n asting three years and killing thousands of people, it began at about 8pm when US Private Willy Grayson shot without provocation an unsuspecting Filipino soldier. The Filipino soldiers quickly returned fire. This was a bloody war that everyone agrees could have been prevented had calmer spirit and more sober mind ruled.', 'May China and Filipino navy personnel manning the opposite sides of the West Philippine Sea refrain from emotional and triggered-happy firing upon each other. May our diplomats keep their cool in dealing with representatives from other countries.', 'Starting a quarrel is like breaching a dam; so drop the matter before a dispute breaks out. <br/>\r\n–<b>Proverbs 17:14</b>', '<i>In human history, we can see sparkles of God\'s redeeming stories</i><br/>\r\n- Pastor Jose Tacadena', 'https://bit.ly/2LXHxpv', 1, NULL, 'We have to admit that we all need to refrain from being irritable, ill-tempered and vindicative to avoid our own battles. We must strive to keep peace with others.');
INSERT INTO `glimpse` (`id`, `title`, `glimpse_date`, `heading`, `content`, `prayer_focus`, `featured_verse`, `featured_quote`, `image_link`, `type`, `created_at`, `transition`) VALUES
(128, '2021-02-05', '2021-02-05', 'On The Launching Of Reader\'s Digest by Dewitt Wallace, A Presbyterian Pastor\'s Son.', 'In 1922, the Reader\'s Digest was launched in New York by Dewitt Wallace, a Presbyterian Pastor\'s son.<br/><br/>\r\n\r\n This monthly general-interest family magazine, with an initial subscription of 1,500 offered condensed articles from the leading magazines. It was the best-selling consumer magazine for many years, reaching additional 40 million readers in at least 70 countries through 49 editions in 21 languages. <br/><br/>\r\n\r\n With a worldwide circulation of 10.5 million, Reader\'s Digest, carrying the slogans, "America in your pocket" and "Life We Shared", is the largest paid circulation magazine in the world.\r\n', 'May Reader\'s Digest keep its legacy and subscription base amidst the internet-laden and highly competitive media world. May publishers, editors and writers specialize in positive entertainment and inspirational articles and media outputs.', 'How sweet are your words to my taste, sweeter than honey to my mouth. <br/>\r\n- <b>Psalms 119:103 </b>', '<i>In human history, we can see sparkles of God\'s redeeming stories</i><br/>\r\n- Pastor Jose Tacadena','https://bit.ly/39Jv2pL', 0, NULL, 'While we should appreciate wholesome and family-oriented publications, we should never neglect the Word of God. After all, the Bible\'s message are edifying in the inmost sense. We must appreciate the Bible as the most spiritually satisfying book.'),
(129, '2021-02-05', '2021-02-05', 'On Leo Echegaray Being the First Filipino to Be Executed Through Lethal Injection.', 'In 1999, Leo Echegaray, became the first Filipino to be executed through lethal injection after the death penalty was reinstated in the Philippines in 1993. <br/><br/>\r\n\r\n The 38-years old house painter was found guilty of raping his 10-years old daughter in 1994. He was given the death penalty by branch 104 of the Regional Trial Court in Quezon City on September 7, 1994. <br/><br/>\r\n\r\n The Supreme Court affirmed the judgment in 1996, and denied Echegaray\'s appeal on January 19, 1999. His death ignited a national debate over the legality and morality of the death penalty, which was eventually suspended on April 15, 2006.', 'May rape and other heinous crimes be prevented, and its perpetrators quickly apprehended and punished according to the law. May God\'s perfect will prevail in the attempt of some quarters to restore the death penalty in our law system.', 'Anyone who kills a person is to be put to death as murderer only on the testimony of witnesses. But no one is to be put to death on the testimony of only one witness. 31 Do not accept a ransom for the life of a murderer, who derives to die. They are to be put to death. <br/>\r\n–<b>Numbers 35:30-31</b>', '<i>In human history, we can see sparkles of God\'s redeeming stories</i><br/>\r\n- Pastor Jose Tacadena', 'https://bit.ly/3bTVeRs', 1, NULL, 'It might internet many to know that during the Old testament times, it was God Himself who commanded death penalty to certain "criminals." We must strive to refrain from committing criminal offences and support the government\'s battle against crimes.'),
(130, '2021-02-06', '2021-02-06', 'On Elizabeth Becoming Queen of Great Britain and Northern Ireland.', 'In 1952, Elizabeth, first child of King George VI of Great Britain and Northern Ireland became a queen.<br/><br/>\r\n\r\n This was after his father died in that day. <br/><br/>\r\n\r\n In the process, she also became the queen of entire commonwealth which then included Canada, Australia, New Zealand, South Africa, Pakistan and Ceylon (Sri Lanka). Her formal reign begun on June 2, 1953 at 27 years old. Today, she is the longest reigning British monarch and the world\'s longest-reigning queen and female head of state.\r\n', 'May she and the other living monarchs in the world enhance their legacy as good and right heads. May Great Britain continue to be nation that promotes democracy and belief in God.', 'Then Esther sent this reply to Mordecai: "Go, gather together all the Jews who are in Susa, and fast for me. Do not eat or drink for three days, night or day. I and my attendants will fast as you do. When this is done, I will go to the king, even though it is against the law. And if I perish, I perish". <br/>\r\n- <b>Esther 4:15-16 </b>', '<i>In human history, we can see sparkles of God\'s redeeming stories</i><br/>\r\n- Pastor Jose Tacadena','https://bit.ly/3602cR0', 0, NULL, 'Esther a Jewish lady who was crowned beauty queen during the time of King Ahasuerus (Xerxes). She was later made the latter\'s queen after Queen Vashti was removed due to her pride and disrespect for the said king. Her greatness as queen was put in a capsule by her concern to work out things as result of His people\'s united prayers, and her readiness to die for this cause. We must strive to manifest concern for our countrymen and faith in God for them.'),
(131, '2021-02-06', '2021-02-06', 'On Philippines Becoming A Virtual American Possession with The Ratification of Treaty Of Paris. <br/><br/>\r\n\r\n In 1899, the Philippines became a virtual American possession with the ratification of the treaty of Paris. <br/><br/>\r\n\r\n It provided that Spain would cede the Philippines to the US which would pay the Spaniards $20M for the improvements made in our country. At first, many American senators opposed that treaty, agreeing that it was unfair to the Filipinos. But the start of the Philippine-US hostilities on February 4 led to its ratification.', 'While offering us the hand of friendship and declaring that they are our \'Big Brother\', the Americans were already set on ruling and manipulating us.', 'May the US-Philippine relations develop some more to the benefit of both parties. May our government and leaders be more discerning to the manipulations of more powerful countries out to abuse and use us and our resources. May we all become genuine friends who truly care for others.', '<i>"Greater love has no one than this: to lay down one\'s life for one\'s friends. 14You are my friends if you do what I command". </i><br/>\r\n–<b>John 15:13</b>', '<i>In human history, we can see sparkles of God\'s redeeming stories</i><br/>\r\n- Pastor Jose Tacadena', 'https://bit.ly/2Kxx5Vk', 1, NULL, 'This story was a bitter lesson on friendship and betrayal. True friendship don\'t manipulate; they liberate. We must strive to be sacrificial for our friends; and obedient to God if we want His total friendship.');
INSERT INTO `glimpse` (`id`, `title`, `glimpse_date`, `heading`, `content`, `prayer_focus`, `featured_verse`, `featured_quote`, `image_link`, `type`, `created_at`, `transition`) VALUES
(132, '2021-02-07', '2021-02-07', 'On The Arrival Of Beatles At The New York Kennedy Airport. <br/><br/>\r\n\r\n In 1964, the "Beatle-mania" arrived in the USA after the original "Fab Four" from Britain landed at the New York Kennedy airport.<br/><br/>', 'The British rock-and-roll quarter of Paul McCartney (21), Ringo Starr (23), John Lennon (23) and George Harrison (20) made their appearance two days later on the Ed Sullivan Show wherein an estimated 73 million US TV viewers watched. That\'s about 40% of the entire US population. Beatles had their first concert in the US on February 11 at the Coliseum in Washington, DC. attended by more than 20,000 fans. <br/><br/>\r\n\r\n Their singles and record albums sold millions of copies each. And their world-wide concerts were all sold-outs. They eventually made box office hit movies. Beatlemania for years indeed.\r\n', 'May today\'s showbiz idols and celebrities excel not only their artistic and theatrical skills but also in being good role models. May everyone, include youths, learn to respect God and live according to His will, aware of coming judgment.', 'Now all has been heard; here is the conclusion of the matter: Fear God and keep his commandments, for this is the duty of all mankind. 14 For God will bring every deed into judgment, including every hidden thing, whether it is good or evil. <br/>\r\n- <b>Proverbs 12:13-14 </b>', '<i>In human history, we can see sparkles of God\'s redeeming stories</i><br/>\r\n- Pastor Jose Tacadena','https://bit.ly/3qCydq7', 0, NULL, 'This was the clear directive by King Solomon to us the Holy Spirit\'s inspiration. We must strive to serve God as much as we can.'),
(133, '2021-02-07', '2021-02-07', 'On Comelec\'s Presidential and Vice-Presidential Snap Elections.<br/><br/>\r\n\r\n In 1886, a Presidential and Vice-Presidential snap elections was held by the COMELEC.', 'This was after then incumbent president Ferdinand Marcos appeared to have given in to international community pressure to prove that he still had the Filipinos\' mandate and called for this election. He fought alongside his Vice-Presidential candidate Arturo Tolentino, former Senate President, against the tandem of former Senator Ninoy Aquino\'s widow, madam Corazon Cojuangco and her running mate Jose Laurel. <br/><br/>\r\n\r\n Batasan Pambansa, which many perceived to be controlled by Pres. Marcos, proclaimed him and his party-mate as winners. But the succeeding events led to the People Power Revolution, the installation of Cory Aquino and the ouster of Pres. Marcos.', 'May the Philippines\' elections be done peacefully, orderly, and justly. May we all be wiser in electing our leaders, basing our choice on the candidates\' character, integrity, tract record and technical qualifications in that order: not in popularity.', 'Like a roaring lion or a charging bear is a wicked ruler over a helpless people. 16 A tyrannical ruler practices extortion, but one who hates ill-gotten gain will enjoy a long reign. <br/>\r\n–<b> Proverbs 28:15-16</b>', '<i>In human history, we can see sparkles of God\'s redeeming stories</i><br/>\r\n- Pastor Jose Tacadena', 'https://bit.ly/3o4QOJA', 1, NULL, 'In electing our leaders, we need to avoid choosing wicked and corrupt people. We must strive to choose only righteous leaders.'),
(134, '2021-02-08', '2021-02-08', 'On The Beginning Of Russian-Japanese War.', 'In 1904, the Russo-Japanese war begun.<br/><br/>\r\n\r\n This was after Russia rejected the Japanese offer to recognize Russian dominance in Manchuria (Northeast Asia that is the region between China and Russia) in exchange for the Japanese domination of Korea. Japan immediately launched a surprise attack against Port Arthur, a Russian naval base in China. The Russian fleet was destroyed. In March, they beat the Russian troops in Shenyang, China, and in May, another Russian fleet was decimated. <br/><br/>\r\n\r\n This war ended on September 5, 1905, with Japan becoming the first modern non-Western world power, boosting its ego towards greater imperial extension.\r\n', 'May Russian and Japan develop its relationship, as well as Japan and China. May China refrain from its territorial expansion of the seas especially at the expense of smaller Asian nations.', 'Cursed be anyone who moves his neighbor\'s landmark and all the people shall say,\ "Amen.". <br/>\r\n- <b>Deuteronomy 27:17 </b>', '<i>In human history, we can see sparkles of God\'s redeeming stories</i><br/>\r\n- Pastor Jose Tacadena','https://bit.ly/3qzewPO', 0, NULL, 'While some countries are too imperialistic and powerful to be prevented from unjustly expanding their territories, we must remember that the Bible is against it. This applies also to individuals encroaching on the rights of others. We must strive to others\' right and territories.'),
(135, '2021-02-08', '2021-02-08', 'On The Approval of The Philippine Constitution.', 'In 1935, the Philippine constitution was approved by the delegates to the constitutional convention. <br/><br/>\r\n\r\n This was after about seven months of deliberation among its 202 members that began on July 30, 1934. They were led by Senator Claro M. Recto as their convention president. The convention delegates signed the final draft on February 19. It was certified by US Pres. Theodore Roosevelt on March 23, 1935 as in line with the Tydings – McDuffie Act. On May 14 that year, it was ratified by the Filipinos through a plebiscite. <br/><br/>\r\n\r\n Based on the U.S. Constitution and the Bill of Rights, this facilitated the ending of the commonwealth government under the Americans and our eventual gaining of national independence later.', 'May more Filipino intellectuals become nationalistic constitutionalists. May corrupt and self-serving politicians in the congress and senate have the decency not to temper our constitution for their own advantage. May those who really love our country defend the main core of our constitution that is really beneficial to our people.', 'Blessed is the nation whose God is the Lord the people He chose for His inheritance. <br/>\r\n–<b> Psalm 33:12</b>', '<i>In human history, we can see sparkles of God\'s redeeming stories</i><br/>\r\n- Pastor Jose Tacadena', 'https://bit.ly/2XXd65p', 1, NULL, 'While a good constitution will always be beneficial to a nation, it is their collective recognition of God that ensures their progress. We must strive to become good and righteous citizens.');
INSERT INTO `glimpse` (`id`, `title`, `glimpse_date`, `heading`, `content`, `prayer_focus`, `featured_verse`, `featured_quote`, `image_link`, `type`, `created_at`, `transition`) VALUES
(136, '2021-02-09', '2021-02-09', 'On The Beginning Of The Davis Cup, The Leading International Team Events in Tennis.', 'In 1990, Davis cup, the leading international team event in tennis, also called the "World Cup of Tennis" began.<br/><br/>\r\n\r\n It was named after then American inter-collegiate singles tennis champion Dwight Davis who convinced the US National Lawn tennis Association to host this tournament in Massachusetts. It pitted Davis\' Harvard tennis team against the top three British tennis players which the hosts beat, 3-0. <br/><br/>\r\n\r\n Today, 135 nations participate in this knock-out format of three games run by the International Tennis Federation. It has two singles matches on the first and the third days, and the second day features a doubles match.\r\n', 'May international sports competition like the Davis Cup truly promote not only sportsmanship and skills development and appreciation, but also genuine camaraderie and partnership.', 'for physical training is of some value, but godliness has value for all things, holding promise for both the present life and the life to come. <br/>\r\n- <b>1 Timothy 4:8 </b>', '<i>In human history, we can see sparkles of God\'s redeeming stories</i><br/>\r\n- Pastor Jose Tacadena','https://bit.ly/2M5zJCa', 0, NULL, 'Sports Competition like Davis Cup bring us to at least two vital truth – the importance of the following the rules to qin, and the godliness as a more valuable form of spiritual exercise. We must strive to exercise not only our body but more so our soul through godliness.'),
(137, '2021-02-09', '2021-02-09', 'On The Establishment Of Central Bank Council and The Foundation For The First Monetary Authority In The Philippines.', 'In 1948, the Central Bank Council and The Foundation for the First Monetary Authority in the country was established with finance secretary Miguel Cuaderno as its leader. <br/><br/>\r\n\r\n This was under the directive of then Pres. Manuel Roxas who instructed Cuaderno to make a charter for the said central bank. This charter was approved by the Congress on this day. This led the next president, Elpidio Quirino to sign the Pe. Act No.265 (Central Bank Act of 1948) on January 3, 1949, the first Central Bank of the Philippines was formally inaugurated with Miguel Cuaderno as its first governor. <br/><br/>\r\n\r\n On July 3, 1993, the New Central Bank Act was signed paving the way for the \'upgrading\' of this bank to become the Banko Sentral ng Pilipinas. This New Central New Bank has more power and autonomy than the previous one.', 'May the BSP improve further as effective tool for the national financial management and economic development. May it lead other banks to encourage the Filipinos to manage their finances well and save for the future.', 'But store up for yourselves treasure in heaven, go where moths and vermin do not destroy, and where thieves do not break in and steal. <br/>\r\n–<b> Matthew 6:20</b>', '<i>In human history, we can see sparkles of God\'s redeeming stories</i><br/>\r\n- Pastor Jose Tacadena', 'https://bit.ly/35Wlpmn', 1, NULL, 'The concept and principle of fundamental banking is, in a way in line with the Bible. We must strive to de diligent in our work and save for the future and heavenly reward. Of course, more than the finances, we should also prepare for the better aspects of life.'),
(138, '2021-02-10', '2021-02-10', 'On The Exchange Of Captured Spies Between US and Russia.', 'In 1962, the US and Russia exchanged captured spies in Berlin, Germany.<br/><br/>\r\n\r\n The American spy was Francis Gary Power whose CIA U-2 plane photographing Russian military installations, was shot down over the Soviet Union. His Russian counterpart was Colonel Rudolf Abel who had been convicted of espionage in the US. <br/><br/>\r\n\r\n The exchange happened on the Glienicke Bridge between the East and the West Berlin in Germany. It was part of the attempts of US Pres. John F. Kennedy and Russian premier Nikka Khrushchev to further soften the Cold War between the two countries.\r\n', 'May the United States and Russia improve further their relationship. May espionage be prevented among countries, especially those that destroy lives. May China and other superpower nations refrain from spying smaller countries.', 'By faith the prostitute Rahab, because she welcomed the spies, was not killed with those who were disobedient. <br/>\r\n- <b>Hebrews 11:31 </b>', '<i>In human history, we can see sparkles of God\'s redeeming stories</i><br/>\r\n- Pastor Jose Tacadena','https://bit.ly/3p67Loj', 0, NULL, 'One "Spy Story" written in the Bible was about the two Jews sent by Joshua to spy the city of Jericho which they intended to attack. Rahab, a Jericho prostitute, help them to elude being capture and to return to their group. We must strive to exercise our faith in claiming blessings for our people.'),
(139, '2021-02-10', '2021-02-10', 'On The First Holding of World Tourism Meet in The Philippines.','In 1975, the world tourism meet was held in the Philippines for the first time. <br/><br/>\r\n\r\n It was a giant step in letting the world see the beauty of the Philippines. As a result, the international community took notice and began visiting our country frequently since then. <br/><br/>\r\n\r\n We are indeed blessed that in the Philippines, we can claim many times over, "How beautiful our God\'s creations".', 'May world tourism be more accessible to all sorts of people. May the Philippine government continue to improve infrastructures and other needed factors in a truly globally competitive tourism industry. May we all complement the beauty of personalities and character.', 'Those who belong to Christ Jesus have crucified the flesh with its passions and desires. 25 Since we live by the Spirit, let us keep in step with the Spirit. <br/>\r\n–<b>Galatians 5:24-25</b>', '<i>In human history, we can see sparkles of God\'s redeeming stories</i><br/>\r\n- Pastor Jose Tacadena', 'https://bit.ly/3qD1xwH', 1, NULL, 'People who have good characteristics usually attract people the most. St. Paul calls these as the fruits of the Spirit (Galatians 5:22-23) which we manifest as we\'re filled with the Holy Spirit and keep in step with Him. We must strive to live in the Spirit and bear Christian fruits.');
INSERT INTO `glimpse` (`id`, `title`, `glimpse_date`, `heading`, `content`, `prayer_focus`, `featured_verse`, `featured_quote`, `image_link`, `type`, `created_at`, `transition`) VALUES
(140, '2021-02-11', '2021-02-11', 'On Nelson Mandela Being Released From Prison After 27 Years.', 'In 1990, Nelson Mandela, South Africa's anti-apartheid movement leader and Nobel Peace Prize Winne, was released from prison after 27 years.<br/><br/>\r\n\r\n This lawyer who became the head of the African National Congress, the oldest black political group in South Africa, was sentenced to life imprisonment due to sabotage. <br/><br/>\r\n\r\n Even while suffering much human rights abuse in prison, he remained the leader of the black people in his country, and led civil disobedience campaigns against the minority white government. With this pressure, South African President F.W Klerk eventually dismantled apartheid, suspended execution and released Mandela.\r\n', 'May apartheid, the system or institutionalized aggregation, and any of its similar malpractices, be fully prevented in any society. May we learn to respect people regardless of their color, and other personal background.', 'And masters, treat your slaves in the same way. Do not threaten them, since you know that he who is both their Master and yours is in heaven, and there is no favoritism with him. <br/>\r\n- <b>Ephesians 6:9 </b>', '<i>In human history, we can see sparkles of God\'s redeeming stories</i><br/>\r\n- Pastor Jose Tacadena','https://bit.ly/360DArk', 0, NULL, 'May today's masters, employers, or bosses treat their servants and employees well, recognizing that this is the God's will. We must strive to recognized that by treating others well, especially our subordinates, we also please God our Master.'),
(141, '2021-02-11', '2021-02-11', 'On The Release Of Manila Standard\'s Maiden Issue.','In 1987, the Manila\'s Standard, the 2015 newspaper of the year released its maiden issue. <br/><br/>\r\n\r\n This was through the initiatives of Rod Reyes, one of the most prominent newspaper columnists during the dark era of journalism in the Martial Law years of Pres. Ferdinand Marcos. <br/><br/>\r\n\r\n He convinced Manuel Elizalde, Jr. to be the owner of this newspaper, which help office at the Ayala Avenue in Makati. Its initial issue consisted of 19 pages. Now called "The Standard" under a new ownership, this national broadsheet is noted for its balanced reporting on current events and issues.', 'May our newspapers and its staff/owners continue to practice fair and just journalism. May proponents of fake news be caught and penalized accordingly. May we all discern news, articles and social media posts that are either fake or at least damaging to individuals and societies, and eradicate them.', 'For what I received I passed on to you as of first importance that Christ died for our sins according to the Scriptures, 4 that He was buried, that He was raised on the third day according to the Scriptures. <br/>\r\n–<b>1 Corinthians 15:3-4 </b>', '<i>In human history, we can see sparkles of God\'s redeeming stories</i><br/>\r\n- Pastor Jose Tacadena', 'https://bit.ly/35ZWJK5', 1, NULL, 'May we all learn to recognize the good news these days, and value the best good news of all times. The redemptive death of the Lord Jesus Christ on the cross and His triumphant resurrection for our salvation. We must strive to share this Gospel of the Lord Jesus Christ.'),
(142, '2021-02-12', '2021-02-12', 'On The Death Of American cartoonist, Charles Monroe Schulz.', 'In 2000, Charles Monroe Schulz, the American Cartoonist best known for his comic strip, "Peanuts" died from colon cancer.<br/><br/>\r\n\r\n His "Peanuts" characters Charlie Brown and Snoopy became globally famous and were the major reason for him to be regarded as one of the most influential cartoonists of all times. <br/><br/>\r\n\r\n The only child of a German and a Norwegian couple who migrated to Minnesota, USA, his first major drawing was "Spike" (named after their family dog) which eats pins and tacks. His "Spike" drawing were featured by "Ripley's Believe it or Not" in 1937. In high school, his drawings were rejected for inclusion in his high school year book.\r\n', 'May more cartoonists invent characters and stories that are not only hilarious but are also uplifting and inspiring.', 'Even though I walk through the darkest valley, I will fear no evil, for you are with me; your rod and your staff, they comfort me. 6 Surely your goodness and love will follow me all the days of my life and I will dwell in the house of the Lord forever. <br/>\r\n- <b> Psalm 23:4,6</b>', '<i>In human history, we can see sparkles of God\'s redeeming stories</i><br/>\r\n- Pastor Jose Tacadena','https://bit.ly/3iyaXGP', 0, NULL, 'Hopefully, Schulz who instilled countless positive principles and ideas through his stories and characters, faced his own death in faith to his Maker. After all, he is known to be a firm believer in the Bible all his life. And the Bible assures to those who believe in God and His Word about death and after life. We must strive to continue trusting God even during our most trying moments.'),
(143, '2021-02-12', '2021-02-12', 'On The Birth Of Lamberto Avellana of The Philippine Movies and The First National Artist in Theater and Film.','In 1915, Lamberto Avellana of the Philippine Movies" and the first Filipino National Artist in Theatre and Films, was born in Bontoc, Mountain province. <br/><br/>\r\n\r\n Initially a stage director, his first film, "Sakay" (a true story about the Filipino general who fought against the Spanish and American regimes), was declared the Best Picture in 1939. His movies, "Anak Dalita", won the Grand Prix at the Asian Film Festival in Hong Kong in 1956. He himself was chosen as the "Best Director of Asia" in Tokyo Film Festival 1957 for his film, "Badjao". <br/><br/>\r\n\r\n Among his 70 other movies in six decades, "Kalderong Pilak" made him the first Filipino filmmaker to qualify for the Cannes International Film Festival.', 'May our filmmakers continue to promote historical movies that lift up our heroes and culture. May their movies be good tools for highlighting Filipino values and assets, and not on a promotional \'packer\' towards materialism, worldliness and immorality.', 'but test them all; hold on to what is good, 22 reject every kind of evil. <br/>\r\n–<b>1 Thessalonians 5:21-22</b>', '<i>In human history, we can see sparkles of God\'s redeeming stories</i><br/>\r\n- Pastor Jose Tacadena', 'https://bit.ly/3p65l9h', 1, NULL, 'While watching movies in not entirely wrong, we should be vigilant in what we watch and patronized. We must strive to reject any form of evil and employ goodness to ensure our life before God.');
INSERT INTO `glimpse` (`id`, `title`, `glimpse_date`, `heading`, `content`, `prayer_focus`, `featured_verse`, `featured_quote`, `image_link`, `type`, `created_at`, `transition`) VALUES
(144, '2021-02-13', '2021-02-13', 'On The Arrival Of Galileo Galilei In Rome For His Roman Catholic Acquisition.', 'In 1633, Italian Astronomer and Mathematician Galileo Galilei arrived in Rome to face Roman Catholic inquisition.<br/><br/>\r\n\r\n He\'s charged with heresy for advocating the Copernican theory that the Earth revolves around the Sun (The Roman Catholic Church then believed that it\'s the sun that revolves around the Earth). <br/><br/>\r\n\r\n He officially faced in April the inquisition, a group of institutions with the Roman Catholic Church that fought heresy and executed whom they called as heretics. He pled guilty in exchange for a lighter sentence, being put under house arrest for the rest of his life.\r\n', 'May Bible believers be more cautious in making unintelligent conclusions about science-related matters. May science proponents in turn be more respectful to the reliability of the Bible, especially on matters of faith.', 'For every house is built by someone, but God is the builder of everything. <br/>\r\n- <b> Hebrews 3:4</b>', '<i>In human history, we can see sparkles of God\'s redeeming stories</i><br/>\r\n- Pastor Jose Tacadena','https://bit.ly/2XWLBcq', 0, NULL, 'May we all recognize that the pinnacle, God who is the source of all creatures and true science, is the One who inspired the writing of the Sacred Scriptures. We must strive to believe that God created the earth and the entire universe.'),
(145, '2021-02-13', '2021-02-13', 'On The Arrival Of The Miguel Lopez De Legazpi in The Philippines, More Particularly, The Shores Of Present-Day Samar.', 'In 1565, Miguel Lopez de Legazpi, the first Spanish to conquer the Filipino, reached the Philippines, and landed on the shores of the present-day Samar. <br/><br/>\r\n\r\n His fleet of four ships left Mexico on November 21, 1564. His expedition then reached Bohol, Cebu and finally Manila where he established a permanent settlement in Manila. <br/><br/>\r\n\r\n He ruled the Philippines through the sword and the cross, taking advantage on the Filipinos\' divided barangay units to impose Spanish might. He maximized the persuasiveness of the cross to pacify the Filipinos.', 'May ongoing expeditions with good intentions succeed at the quickest possible time for optimum benefits. May the Philippines and Spain continue to develop bilateral relations.', 'Watch out for false prophets. They come to you in sheep's clothing, but inwardly they are ferocious wolves. <br/>\r\n–<b>Matthew 7:15</b>', '<i>In human history, we can see sparkles of God\'s redeeming stories</i><br/>\r\n- Pastor Jose Tacadena', 'https://bit.ly/3qRZSUj', 1, NULL, 'This story teaches us at least two applications. We must strive to be discerning to people who come into our lives, and must promote unity among our peers to oppose intruders and manipulators.'),
(146, '2021-02-14', '2021-02-14', 'On The Discovery Of Sir Alexander Fleming.', 'In 1929, Penicillin was accidentally discovered by Sir Alexander Fleming.<br/><br/>\r\n\r\n The Scottish microbiologists unintentionally left a plate of staphylococcus bacteria without any cover in his laboratory. He noticed that a mold which had fallen on this had killed many of the bacteria. He later identified the mold as penicillin notatum which is similar to that found on bread. He further isolated it to make world's first antibiotic substance benzylpenicillin (Penicillin G) which is in intravenous or injected. <br/><br/>\r\n\r\n It\'s effective against many bacterial infections. For this discovery, Fleming won the Nobel Prize for Medicine in 1945.\r\n', 'May more substances for medicine be discovered and/or manufactured for mass use and benefits. May the recurring epidemics like measles and dengue be prevented.', ' Praise the Lord, my soul, and forget not all his benefits – who forgives all your sin and heals all your diseases. <br/>\r\n- <b> Psalm 103:2-3</b>', '<i>In human history, we can see sparkles of God\'s redeeming stories</i><br/>\r\n- Pastor Jose Tacadena','https://bit.ly/3qCJzdI', 0, NULL, 'While penicillin and other forms of antibiotic are truly helpful, positive attitude is also beneficial for our health. And the recognition that it is God who eventually heals us.  We must strive to recognize that God is the ultimate healer.'),
(147, '2021-02-14', '2021-02-14', 'On The Establishment Of Philippine Heart Center in East Avenue, Quezon City.','In 1975, the Philippine Heart Center was opened in East Avenue, Quezon City. <br/><br/>\r\n\r\n Established through Pres. Decree 673 by Pre. Ferdinand Marcos, it's a hospital and research center that provides comprehensive cardiovascular care enhanced by education and research that is accessible to all. <br/><br/>\r\n\r\n . Its first director was Dr. Avellano Aventura, a cardiovascular surgeon who has pioneered many heart-related operations in the Philippines. It admits more than 14,000 patients yearly, including around 3,000 who undergo heart surgery.', 'May the PHC continue to improve in its facilities, qualified personnel and incentives for his staff. May Filipinos live a healthier lifestyle to avoid having heart ailments. More than the literal hearts, though, may we all learn to value the spiritual heart, the center of thoughts, decisions and actions.', 'Take delight in the Lord, and he will give you the desires of your heart. <br/>\r\n–<b> Proverbs 37:4</b>', '<i>In human history, we can see sparkles of God\'s redeeming stories</i><br/>\r\n- Pastor Jose Tacadena', 'https://bit.ly/39RaGuP', 1, NULL, 'After all, God Himself commands us to give our heart for this is the key to having our heart's desire. We must strive give to God our heart and satisfy Him.');
INSERT INTO `glimpse` (`id`, `title`, `glimpse_date`, `heading`, `content`, `prayer_focus`, `featured_verse`, `featured_quote`, `image_link`, `type`, `created_at`, `transition`) VALUES
(148, '2021-02-15', '2021-02-15', 'On The Sales of The First Teddy Bear in the USA.', 'In 1903, the world\'s first teddy bear went on sale in the USA.<br/><br/>\r\n\r\n This was through Morris Michtom who displayed two stuffed bears in his shops windows, calling them as teddy bears. <br/><br/>\r\n\r\n Before that, US Pres. Theodore Roosevelt allowed him to use his nickname teddy for this toy. Since then, other manufacturers copied Michtom\'s teddy bears, until they became a national childhood institution. Today, teddy bear remains one of the best-selling stuffed toys and gifts in the world. Not only for kids but also for adults to signify love, congratulations or sympathy.\r\n', 'May the kids\' toys industry develop more eco-friendly and pro-health projects. May these toys do not promote violence, selfishness and worldliness, but instead, love and good manners.', 'They found the stone rolled away from the tomb, 3 but when they entered, they did not find the body of the Lord Jesus. <br/>\r\n- <b> Luke 24:2-3 </b>', '<i>In human history, we can see sparkles of God\'s redeeming stories</i><br/>\r\n- Pastor Jose Tacadena','https://bit.ly/3qJCjNl', 0, NULL, 'While people are amazed at the riches of the tombs of kings and other prominent rich personalities, we should even be more amazed that the tomb of the Lord Jesus Christ is empty – for Jesus has resurrected! We must glorify the Lord Jesus Christ for rising from the dead.'),
(149, '2021-02-15', '2021-02-15', 'On The Legislature Passing the Bill Making November 30 as "Andres Bonifacio Day".','In 1921, the Legislature passed the bill making November 30 as "Andres Bonifacio Day". <br/><br/>\r\n\r\n It\'s a fitting tribute to the founder of the KKK and the "Father of Philippine Revolution". He epitomized Filipino courage and live for country and freedom.  It was tragic that he was executed by his own people. <br/><br/>\r\n\r\n Victim of a political struggle for leadership among Pinoy leaders. For years, Bonifacio was even considered by some as a villain for his rift with Gen. Emilio Aguinaldo. With this February 16 legislation, Bonifacio was finally vindicated.', 'May we continue to value and emulate the heroism or Bonifacio and our other heroes. May other heroes who remain obscure before the nation be finally recognized and honored.', 'The righteous will be glad when they are avenged, when they dip their feet in the blood of the wicked. 11 Then people will say, "Surely the righteous still are rewarded: surely there is a God who judges the earth". <br/>\r\n–<b> Psalm 58:10-11</b>', '<i>In human history, we can see sparkles of God\'s redeeming stories</i><br/>\r\n- Pastor Jose Tacadena', 'https://bit.ly/39V8fXY', 1, NULL, 'May we also learn to apply the meaning of La Solidaridad, which is unity and solidarity. And its secret? Christian love. We must strive to demonstrate Christian love towards unity.'),
(150, '2021-02-16', '2021-02-16', 'On Howard Carter Opening the Tomb Of Ancient King Tutankhamun Of Egypt.', 'In 1923, English archaeologist Howard Carter opened the tomb of ancient King Tutankhamun of Egypt.<br/><br/>\r\n\r\n . This was after six years of costly search by Carter\'s team financially backed up by British Lord Carnarvon. They found the chamber of King Tut who lived around 1,400 B.C. on November 26 near the entrance of another tomb. It has four rooms containing all sorts of treasures. <br/><br/>\r\n\r\n The treasures collected from these are now included in the famous exhibit, the treasures of Tutankhamun at the Egyptian Museum in Cairo.\r\n', 'May more archeological and scientific expeditions succeed with relative swiftness so as to maximize the benefits to people concerned. May more advanced equipment and tools be made so as to minimize damage to artifacts and ensure safety to searchers.', 'We all growl like bears… we look for justice, but find none; for deliverance, but it is far away. <br/>\r\n- <b> Isaiah 59:11</b>', '<i>In human history, we can see sparkles of God\'s redeeming stories</i><br/>\r\n- Pastor Jose Tacadena','https://bit.ly/2LLgSwy', 0, NULL, 'While teddy bears became a nice symbol, it's interesting that in the Bible, bears are compared to several kinds of people and actions. We must not imitate the fierceness ad recklessness of bears.'),
(151, '2021-02-16', '2021-02-16', 'On La Solidaridad Being Published in Barcelona, Spain.', 'In 1889, La Solidaridad was first published in Barcelona, Spain by Filipino reformists. <br/><br/>\r\n\r\n This was to promote the interests of Filipinos against Spanish abuses in the Philippines. Appearing every fifteen days, it was initially edited by Graciano Lopez Jaena. <br/><br/>\r\n\r\n . With writers like Jose Rizal, Marcelo del Pilar and Antonio Luna, it inspired Filipinos to continue our fight for freedom.', 'May we continue to recognize the importance of press freedom in promoting peace and progress. May writers, publishers and editors of publications especially those which promote truth, fairness and justice be protected from harassment.', 'and over all these virtues put on love, which binds them all together in perfect unity. <br/>\r\n–<b> Colossians 3:14</b>', '<i>In human history, we can see sparkles of God\'s redeeming stories</i><br/>\r\n- Pastor Jose Tacadena', 'https://bit.ly/391sCnm', 1, NULL, 'May we also learn to apply the meaning of La Solidaridad, which is unity and solidarity. And its secret? Christian love. We must strive to demonstrate Christian love towards unity.');
INSERT INTO `glimpse` (`id`, `title`, `glimpse_date`, `heading`, `content`, `prayer_focus`, `featured_verse`, `featured_quote`, `image_link`, `type`, `created_at`, `transition`) VALUES
(150, '2021-02-17', '2021-02-17', 'On The French and British Navies Battling in The Indian Ocean for America\'s Independence.', 'In 1782, French and British navies battle in the Indian Ocean as part of the American war for independence.<br/><br/>\r\n\r\n France, being allied to the Americans who were then waging an independence war against their British colonizers, began a 14-month series of five battles with Britain. The French were led by Admiral Pierre Andre de Suffren de Saint-Tropez. The British were led by Vice Admiral Sir Edward Hughes, commander in chief in the East Indies. <br/><br/>\r\n\r\n The first four battles did not produce a clear winner though both navies suffered heavy casualties. The fifth and last one on April 20, 1783 – the Battle of Cuddalore, forced the British to leave Madras. The French victory helped in the peace settlement of both countries and the independence of Americans.\r\n', 'May France, Britain and US maintain a developing partnership on all fronts, to the advantage of not only og the three countries but also of the entire democratic world. May more naval battles, including the potential one on West Philippine Seas, be prevented.', 'But thanks be to God! He gives us the victory through our Lord Jesus Christ. <br/>\r\n- <b> 1 Corinthians 15:57</b>', '<i>In human history, we can see sparkles of God\'s redeeming stories</i><br/>\r\n- Pastor Jose Tacadena','https://bit.ly/3qHY1kS', 0, NULL, 'It\'s interesting to note that the French navy was the complete underdog in their naval battle against that much experienced and vastly trained and equipped British forces. Still, they won. A good reminder that underdogs can win, especially if they rely on God. And heavily favored protagonists may still lose, especially if they are overconfident. We must strive to trust God for our personal victories and glorify Him in return.'),
(151, '2021-02-17', '2021-02-17', 'On Fathers Gomez, Burgoz And Zamora Being Garroted. <br/><br/>\r\n\r\n In 1872, Mariano Gomez, Jose Burgoz and Jacinto Zamora, the Gom-Bur-Za trio of Filipino priests were garroted in Bagumbayan (Rizal Park). <br/><br/>\r\n\r\n They were unjustly accused of instigators of the Anti-Spanish Movement which led to the January 21 Cavite Mutiny. Though they were leaders in the National Movement among the native clergy, they were not instigators of violence and rebellion. <br/><br/>\r\n\r\n Filipinos mourned their death. But from it, fresher and more passionate nationalism sprouted, including among the likes of the Jose Rizal and Andres Bonifacio, sealing the executioner\'s fate in due time.', 'May today\'s clergy: priests, pastors, minister and religious leaders have the same zeal of nationalism while keeping their priority of leading the people in serving God. May those in the government do not persecute these clergies, especially if based only on personal opinions. May the separation of church and state as stated in our constitution remain respected.', '<i>"I will place shepherds over them who will tend them, and they will no longer be afraid or terrified, nor will any be missing," declares the Lord. </i><br/>\r\n–<b> Jeremiah 23:4</b>', '<i>In human history, we can see sparkles of God\'s redeeming stories</i><br/>\r\n- Pastor Jose Tacadena', 'https://bit.ly/39N4ZOu', 1, NULL, 'May religious leaders truly preach the Gospel of Jesus and demonstrate love to God and one\'s nation; thereby proving genuine partnership with the Lord. We must strive to appreciate our spiritual leaders and those who make sacrifices for other people and their nation.');
(152, '2021-02-18', '2021-02-18', 'On The Death Of Martin Luther, the "Father Of Protestant Reformation".', 'In 1546, Martin Luther, the "Father of Protestant Reformation", died in Eisleben, Germany at 63 years old.<br/><br/>\r\n\r\n At 22, he joined the Augustinian monastery. At 28, was appointed Professor of Scripture at Wittenberg. There, he learned "that man is justified before God by faith in Jesus, not good works". He also discovered that only the Bible should guide man\'s spiritual life. <br/><br/>\r\n\r\n At 34, Luther posted his 95 Theses, opposing the wrong teachings and practices of the Catholic Church, denouncing the selling of indulgences. He\'s excommunicated and condemned to die. He didn\'t recant until he died.\r\n', 'May religious leaders really decide and determine to search. Teach and apply only what the word of God really teaches. And not just human opinions and traditions. May they refrain from abusing their members but guide and serve them well in the Lord.', 'Do not be afraid of those who kill the body but cannot kill the soul. Rather, be afraid of the one who can destroy both soul and body in hell. <br/>\r\n- <b> Matthew 10:28</b>', '<i>In human history, we can see sparkles of God\'s redeeming stories</i><br/>\r\n- Pastor Jose Tacadena','https://bit.ly/362USUD', 0, NULL, 'May we all recognize what Luther did – that we are saved only by God\'s grace, and must not be afraid, if ever, to dies for Him. We must strive to trust and even in our dying.'),
(153, '2021-02-18', '2021-02-18', 'On The Beautification of Lorenzo Ruiz, Making Him the First Filipino Roman Catholic Saint Later. <br/><br/>\r\n\r\n In 1981, Lorenzo Ruiz was beatified by Pope John Paul ll, leading him to become the first Filipino Roman Catholic saint later. <br/><br/>\r\n\r\n Ruiz was a former Catholic altar boy from Binondo, Manila who was leading a peaceful life with his wife and three kids when he was accused of killing a Spaniard. <br/><br/>\r\n\r\n Force to seek asylum in Japan in 1636, he and his group of some Filipino priests were persecuted and tortured for their Christian religion. He died in Nagasaki on September 29, 1636. Dying without recanting his faith, he was canonized as saint on October 18, 1987.', 'May Christian missionaries be protected from unnecessary persecution and torture from their host countries. May all Christians be truly vomited to live for God, and if necessary, die for Him.', 'For to me to live is Christ and to die is gain. <br/>\r\n–<b> Philippians 1:21</b>', '<i>In human history, we can see sparkles of God\'s redeeming stories</i><br/>\r\n- Pastor Jose Tacadena', 'https://bit.ly/2XYZFCj', 1, NULL, 'While we generally fear dying, we can be certain that is also a blessing for those who live for God. We must strive to live for God to be ready to die for Him if necessary.');
INSERT INTO `glimpse` (`id`, `title`, `glimpse_date`, `heading`, `content`, `prayer_focus`, `featured_verse`, `featured_quote`, `image_link`, `type`, `created_at`, `transition`) VALUES
(152, '2021-02-17', '2021-02-17', 'On The French and British Navies Battling in The Indian Ocean for America\'s Independence.', 'In 1782, French and British navies battle in the Indian Ocean as part of the American war for independence.<br/><br/>\r\n\r\n France, being allied to the Americans who were then waging an independence war against their British colonizers, began a 14-month series of five battles with Britain. The French were led by Admiral Pierre Andre de Suffren de Saint-Tropez. The British were led by Vice Admiral Sir Edward Hughes, commander in chief in the East Indies. <br/><br/>\r\n\r\n The first four battles did not produce a clear winner though both navies suffered heavy casualties. The fifth and last one on April 20, 1783 – the Battle of Cuddalore, forced the British to leave Madras. The French victory helped in the peace settlement of both countries and the independence of Americans.\r\n', 'May France, Britain and US maintain a developing partnership on all fronts, to the advantage of not only og the three countries but also of the entire democratic world. May more naval battles, including the potential one on West Philippine Seas, be prevented.', 'But thanks be to God! He gives us the victory through our Lord Jesus Christ. <br/>\r\n- <b> 1 Corinthians 15:57</b>', '<i>In human history, we can see sparkles of God\'s redeeming stories</i><br/>\r\n- Pastor Jose Tacadena','https://bit.ly/3qHY1kS', 0, NULL, 'It\'s interesting to note that the French navy was the complete underdog in their naval battle against that much experienced and vastly trained and equipped British forces. Still, they won. A good reminder that underdogs can win, especially if they rely on God. And heavily favored protagonists may still lose, especially if they are overconfident. We must strive to trust God for our personal victories and glorify Him in return.'),
(153, '2021-02-17', '2021-02-17', 'On Fathers Gomez, Burgoz And Zamora Being Garroted.', 'In 1872, Mariano Gomez, Jose Burgoz and Jacinto Zamora, the Gom-Bur-Za trio of Filipino priests were garroted in Bagumbayan (Rizal Park). <br/><br/>\r\n\r\n They were unjustly accused of instigators of the Anti-Spanish Movement which led to the January 21 Cavite Mutiny. Though they were leaders in the National Movement among the native clergy, they were not instigators of violence and rebellion. <br/><br/>\r\n\r\n Filipinos mourned their death. But from it, fresher and more passionate nationalism sprouted, including among the likes of the Jose Rizal and Andres Bonifacio, sealing the executioner\'s fate in due time.', 'May today\'s clergy: priests, pastors, minister and religious leaders have the same zeal of nationalism while keeping their priority of leading the people in serving God. May those in the government do not persecute these clergies, especially if based only on personal opinions. May the separation of church and state as stated in our constitution remain respected.', '<i>"I will place shepherds over them who will tend them, and they will no longer be afraid or terrified, nor will any be missing," declares the Lord. </i><br/>\r\n–<b> Jeremiah 23:4</b>', '<i>In human history, we can see sparkles of God\'s redeeming stories</i><br/>\r\n- Pastor Jose Tacadena', 'https://bit.ly/39N4ZOu', 1, NULL, 'May religious leaders truly preach the Gospel of Jesus and demonstrate love to God and one\'s nation; thereby proving genuine partnership with the Lord. We must strive to appreciate our spiritual leaders and those who make sacrifices for other people and their nation.'),
(154, '2021-02-18', '2021-02-18', 'On The Death Of Martin Luther, the "Father Of Protestant Reformation".', 'In 1546, Martin Luther, the "Father of Protestant Reformation", died in Eisleben, Germany at 63 years old.<br/><br/>\r\n\r\n At 22, he joined the Augustinian monastery. At 28, was appointed Professor of Scripture at Wittenberg. There, he learned "that man is justified before God by faith in Jesus, not good works". He also discovered that only the Bible should guide man\'s spiritual life. <br/><br/>\r\n\r\n At 34, Luther posted his 95 Theses, opposing the wrong teachings and practices of the Catholic Church, denouncing the selling of indulgences. He\'s excommunicated and condemned to die. He didn\'t recant until he died.\r\n', 'May religious leaders really decide and determine to search. Teach and apply only what the word of God really teaches. And not just human opinions and traditions. May they refrain from abusing their members but guide and serve them well in the Lord.', 'Do not be afraid of those who kill the body but cannot kill the soul. Rather, be afraid of the one who can destroy both soul and body in hell. <br/>\r\n- <b> Matthew 10:28</b>', '<i>In human history, we can see sparkles of God\'s redeeming stories</i><br/>\r\n- Pastor Jose Tacadena','https://bit.ly/362USUD', 0, NULL, 'May we all recognize what Luther did – that we are saved only by God\'s grace, and must not be afraid, if ever, to dies for Him. We must strive to trust and even in our dying.'),
(155, '2021-02-18', '2021-02-18', 'On The Beautification of Lorenzo Ruiz, Making Him the First Filipino Roman Catholic Saint Later.', 'In 1981, Lorenzo Ruiz was beatified by Pope John Paul ll, leading him to become the first Filipino Roman Catholic saint later. <br/><br/>\r\n\r\n Ruiz was a former Catholic altar boy from Binondo, Manila who was leading a peaceful life with his wife and three kids when he was accused of killing a Spaniard. <br/><br/>\r\n\r\n Force to seek asylum in Japan in 1636, he and his group of some Filipino priests were persecuted and tortured for their Christian religion. He died in Nagasaki on September 29, 1636. Dying without recanting his faith, he was canonized as saint on October 18, 1987.', 'May Christian missionaries be protected from unnecessary persecution and torture from their host countries. May all Christians be truly vomited to live for God, and if necessary, die for Him.', 'For to me to live is Christ and to die is gain. <br/>\r\n–<b> Philippians 1:21</b>', '<i>In human history, we can see sparkles of God\'s redeeming stories</i><br/>\r\n- Pastor Jose Tacadena', 'https://bit.ly/2XYZFCj', 1, NULL, 'While we generally fear dying, we can be certain that is also a blessing for those who live for God. We must strive to live for God to be ready to die for Him if necessary.'); 
INSERT INTO `glimpse` (`id`, `title`, `glimpse_date`, `heading`, `content`, `prayer_focus`, `featured_verse`, `featured_quote`, `image_link`, `type`, `created_at`, `transition`) VALUES
(156, '2021-02-19', '2021-02-19', 'On The Birth Of Nicolaus Copernicus, the "Father of Modern Astronomy".', 'In 1473, Nicolaus Copernicus, the “Father of Modern Astronomy”, was born in Torun, Poland.<br/><br/>\r\n\r\n A German polyglot (one who uses several languages) and a polymath (one with numerous skills and learnings), he had a doctorate in canon law, a mathematician, astronomer, physician, translator, governor, and diplomat. <br/><br/>\r\n\r\n He\'s the first European scientist who formulated the model that opposed then the Earth is the center of the Universe and that the sun, moon and planets revolve around our planet. His heliocentric model teaches that it is instead the sun which is the center of the universe. He wrote a book, "Six Books Concerning the Revolutionary Orbs" which he delayed publication due to much contrary pressure.\r\n', 'May more scientists discover more accurate findings on science, that will improve our lives. May our scientific understandings do not alienate us from supreme Creator and God.', 'When I consider your heavens, the work of your fingers the moon and the stars, which you have set in place 4 what is mankind that you are mindful of them human beings that you care for them? <br/>\r\n- <b> Psalm 8:3-4</b>', '<i>In human history, we can see sparkles of God\'s redeeming stories</i><br/>\r\n- Pastor Jose Tacadena','https://bit.ly/3bXUGKf', 0, NULL, 'While we are amazed at the wonders of the Solar System, and admire the scientists that explore them, we must not forget that all of these celestial bodies are but the creation of God. God for His creations and His care for humanity.'),
(157, '2021-02-19', '2021-02-19', 'On The Birth Of Philippine Martyr, Jose Abad Santos, the Fifth Supreme Court Chief Justice.', 'In 1886, Jose Abad Santos, the Fifth Supreme Court Chief Justice, who became a martyr for the Philippines was born in Pampanga. <br/><br/>\r\n\r\n He was appointed as Justice Secretary in 1938 and Chief Justice of the Supreme Court after the war with the Japanese began in 1941. He\'s assigned caretaker of the Commonwealth Government when Pres. Manuel Quezon went into self-exile in 1942. <br/><br/>\r\n\r\n When he was arrested by the Japanese, he was offered many incentives and later, threats to lure him to cooperate with the Japanese in colonizing the Filipinos. He didn\'t, so he was executed.', 'May our lawyers and judges stay God-fearing and nationalistic, and continue to serve our country amidst the lure and unlawful incentives and threats, especially for the manipulative foreigners. May the justice system in the country develop further and maintain independence form the executive and legislative branches of the government.', 'And I charged your judges at that time, <i>"Hear the disputes between your people and judge fairly, whether the case is between two Israelites or between an Israelite and a foreigner residing among you. 17 Do not show partiality in judging; hear both small and great alike. Do not be afraid of anyone, for judgment belongs to God. Bring me any case too hard for you, and I will hear it." </i> <br/>\r\n–<b> Philippians 1:21</b>', '<i>In human history, we can see sparkles of God\'s redeeming stories</i><br/>\r\n- Pastor Jose Tacadena', 'https://bit.ly/3p95sko', 1, NULL, 'God wants judges to be diligent and fair in their tasks. And He is willing to give them wisdom and courage to decide correctly. We must appreciate righteous judges and leaders; and strive to be righteous ourselves.'),
(158, '2021-02-20', '2021-02-20', 'On John Glenn Becoming The First American To Orbit The Earth.', 'In 1962, Lt. Col. John Glenn became the first American to orbit the earth.<br/><br/>\r\n\r\n That was after he circled the Earth tree times that day in the capsule they named, "Friendship 7". <br/><br/>\r\n\r\n He\'s one of the first seven astronauts of America in 1959. Later, Glenn received the NASA Distinguished Service Medal in 1962, the Congressional Space Medal of Honor in 1978, and the US Astronaut Hall of Fame in 1990.\r\n', 'May more astronauts be selected and trained thoroughly not only in terms of skills but also in character. May space technology improve further.', 'Then will appear the sign of the Son of Man in heaven. And then all the peoples of the earth will mourn when they see the Son of Man coming on the clouds of heaven, with power and great glory. 31 And he will send his angels with a loud trumpet call, and they will gather his elect from the four winds, from one end of the heavens to the other. <br/>\r\n- <b> Matthew 24:30-31 </b>', '<i>In human history, we can see sparkles of God\'s redeeming stories</i><br/>\r\n- Pastor Jose Tacadena', 'https://bit.ly/3bVDQM1', 0, NULL, 'Jesus Christ will orbit the Earth in full view of mankind. It will be the sign of His impending return to our planet and the final step in actually landing here again. We must strive to be ready for the return of the Lord Jesus Christ.'),
(159, '2021-02-20', '2021-02-20', 'On The Death Of Francisco Baltazar, The "Prince Of Tagalog Poets".', 'In 1862, Francisco Baltazar, the "Prince of Tagalog Poets", died at 73 years old. <br/><br/>\r\n\r\n Best known as Francisco Balagtas for his masterpiece novel, "Florante at Laura", he was born on April 2, 1788 in Bigaa, Bulacan. <br/><br/>\r\n\r\n He's also called, "Ang Hari ng mga Makata" and considered by many, including well known poets like him, as the William Shakespeare of the Philippines. One more proof of him being revered so much in Philippine literature as the Filipino term for debate in extemporaneous verse attributed to him – Balagtasan.', 'May poetry become more acceptable to the general masses. May more Filipino poets excel and help the society become more analytical and positive about life.', 'Let my teaching fall like rain and my words descend like dew like showers on new grass, like abundant rain on tender plants. <br/>\r\n–<b> Deuteronomy 32:2</b>', '<i>In human history, we can see sparkles of God\'s redeeming stories</i><br/>\r\n- Pastor Jose Tacadena', 'https://bit.ly/39440dB', 1, NULL, 'Do you know that the Word of God is also a kind of beautiful and soothing poetry? We must strive to use our communication and words to the edification of others.');
INSERT INTO `glimpse` (`id`, `title`, `glimpse_date`, `heading`, `content`, `prayer_focus`, `featured_verse`, `featured_quote`, `image_link`, `type`, `created_at`, `transition`) VALUES
(160, '2021-02-21', '2021-02-21', 'On The Assassination Of Malcom Little (Malcolm X), an African-American Nationalist and Religious leader.', 'In 1965, Malcolm Little, better known as Malcolm X, an African-American Nationalist and Religious leader, was assassinated. <br/><br/>\r\n\r\n His three assailants were rival Black Muslims who shot him while he was addressing his Organization of Afro-American Unity at the Audubon Ballroom in Washington Heights. <br/><br/>\r\n\r\n He became a member of the Nation of Islam while imprisoned at 21 years old for burglary. This group advocated for black supremacy, and condemned white Americans as devils. Later, he got disillusioned with the black Islam and disavowed racism, getting the Ire of the leaders of this group. Today, he\'s considered as one of the greatest African-American leaders in history.\r\n', 'May racial discrimination be totally eradicated in the world. May those who have grievances against the government do it in a lawful way and refrain from espousing violence. May assassination attempts be prevented early on.', 'But the Lord said to Samuel, <i> "Do not consider his appearance or his height, for I have rejected him. The Lord does not look at the things people look at. People look at the outward appearance, but the Lord looks at the heart\". </i><br/>\r\n- <b> 1 Samuel 16:7 </b>', '<i>In human history, we can see sparkles of God\'s redeeming stories</i><br/>\r\n- Pastor Jose Tacadena', 'https://bit.ly/3p9Sove', 0, NULL, 'We must always remember that we should not base our treatment of others on their physical features and skin color. We must strive not to be judgmental with others based on their outward looks.'),
(161, '2021-02-21', '2021-02-21', 'On The Birth Of Felix Hidalgo, one the Greatest Filipino Painters.', 'In 1855, Felix Hidalgo, one of the greatest Filipino Painters, was born in Binondo, Manila. <br/><br/>\r\n\r\n He took up Fine Arts and was sent to Spain in 1879 as scholar, finishing the course at the school of Fine arts in Madrid. He stayed in Paris and put up a gallery. This became a center of Filipino activities and gathering, encouraging exiles and revolutionaries like Dr. Jose Rizal and Marcelo del Pillar. <br/><br/>\r\n\r\n He produced over a thousand drawings and painting including those which the Spanish government commissioned in return for his scholarship. He won the silver medal I the 1884 Madrid Exposition of Arts, and the gold at the Universal Exposition in St. Louis Missouri in 1904.', 'May more Filipino painters and artists living abroad excel and promote the Philippines and our culture. May their residence abroad be a safe haven for other Filipinos there.', 'For we are God\'s handiwork created in Christ Jesus to do good works which God prepared in advance for us to do. <br/>\r\n–<b> Deuteronomy 32:2</b>', '<i>In human history, we can see sparkles of God\'s redeeming stories</i><br/>\r\n- Pastor Jose Tacadena', 'https://bit.ly/394W8c0', 1, NULL, 'We appreciate artists who make masterpieces, whether this is painting, or sculpt or story, or music. This is why we should worship God all the more because His greatest masterpiece is no less than the Christians. We must strive to abound in good works as our tribute to God our Maker.'),
(162, '2021-02-22', '2021-02-22', 'On Military Dictator Gen. Hajji Mohammad Suharto Taking Full Power In Indonesia.', 'In 1967, then  military dictator Gen. Hajji Mohammad Suharto took full power in Indonesia. <br/><br/>\r\n\r\n That was after their President Sukarno surrendered all his executive authority to the general who saved him from a communist coup in 1965. But in the process, the general replaced the elected president and purged communists, killing thousands. In 1968, the general was elected president himself. <br/><br/>\r\n\r\n He was re-elected every five years until his forced resignation in 1998. He was able to stabilize Indonesia, and to push national economic growth.\r\n', 'May Indonesia continue to progress and improve its relations with other countries. Ma it prevent any more coup attempts. May it refrain from persecuting its Christian citizens and missionaries.', 'Praise be to the name of God for ever and ever; wisdom and power are his. 21 He changes times and seasons; he deposes kings and raises up others. He gives wisdom to the wise and knowledge to the discerning. <br/>\r\n- <b> Daniel 2:20-21 </b>', '<i>In human history, we can see sparkles of God\'s redeeming stories</i><br/>\r\n- Pastor Jose Tacadena', 'https://bit.ly/3a05QM2', 0, NULL, 'The prophet Daniel, who lived during the times of one of the greatest kings of all times, knew that behind the rise and fall of kings is God who is Sovereign; and who provides leadership ability to those who submit to Him.'),
(163, '2021-02-22', '2021-02-22', 'On US Pres. Roosevelt Ordering Gen. MacArthur To Move Out Of The Philippines.', 'In 1942, US President Franklin Roosevelt ordered Gen. Douglas McArthur. . <br/><br/>\r\n\r\n This was after the American defense of the American defense of the Philippines collapsed on the onslaught of the Japanese attack. He was earlier called out of retirement to command 10,000 US troops, 12, 000 Filipino enlisted men who fought as part of the US Army and 100, 000 poorly trained and ill-equipped Filipino army soldiers to defend the Philippines. <br/><br/>\r\n\r\n With MacArthur\'s forces retreating to Bataan on late December, 1941, and the fall of Manila on Jan 2 to the Japanese, President Roosevelt felt he could not afford to lose the general.', 'May the Philippines come up with better defense plan of its territory especially with the communist Chinese encroaching in on the West Philippine Sea and on other areas subtly. May the Armed Forces of the Philippines acquire better technology, weapons, ships, planes and training.', 'Do not conform to the pattern of this world, but be transformed by the renewing of your mind. <br/>\r\n–<b> Romans 12:2a</b>', '<i>In human history, we can see sparkles of God\'s redeeming stories</i><br/>\r\n- Pastor Jose Tacadena', 'https://bit.ly/2LY1rRv', 1, NULL, ' Just like Pres. Roosevelt and Gen. MacArthur, may we all learn to move out when needed. God Himself wants Christians to move out of the worldly system.');
INSERT INTO `glimpse` (`id`, `title`, `glimpse_date`, `heading`, `content`, `prayer_focus`, `featured_verse`, `featured_quote`, `image_link`, `type`, `created_at`, `transition`) VALUES
(164, '2021-02-23', '2021-02-23', 'On Military Dictator Gen. Hajji Mohammad Suharto Taking Full Power In Indonesia.', 'In 1967, then  military dictator Gen. Hajji Mohammad Suharto took full power in Indonesia. <br/><br/>\r\n\r\n That was after their President Sukarno surrendered all his executive authority to the general who saved him from a communist coup in 1965. But in the process, the general replaced the elected president and purged communists, killing thousands. In 1968, the general was elected president himself. <br/><br/>\r\n\r\n He was re-elected every five years until his forced resignation in 1998. He was able to stabilize Indonesia, and to push national economic growth.\r\n', 'May Indonesia continue to progress and improve its relations with other countries. May it prevent any more coup attempts. May it refrain from persecuting its Christian citizens and missionaries.', 'Praise be to the name of God for ever and ever; wisdom and power are his. 21 He changes times and seasons; he deposes kings and raises up others. He gives wisdom to the wise and knowledge to the discerning. <br/>\r\n- <b> Daniel 2:20-21 </b>', '<i>In human history, we can see sparkles of God\'s redeeming stories</i><br/>\r\n- Pastor Jose Tacadena', 'https://bit.ly/3a05QM2', 0, NULL, 'The prophet Daniel, who lived during the times of one of the greatest kings of all times, knew that behind the rise and fall of kings is God who is Sovereign; and who provides leadership ability to those who submit to Him.'),
(165, '2021-02-23', '2021-02-23', 'On US Pres. Roosevelt Ordering Gen. MacArthur To Move Out Of The Philippines.', 'In 1942, US President Franklin Roosevelt ordered Gen. Douglas McArthur. <br/><br/>\r\n\r\n This was after the American defense of the American defense of the Philippines collapsed on the onslaught of the Japanese attack. He was earlier called out of retirement to command 10,000 US troops, 12, 000 Filipino enlisted men who fought as part of the US Army and 100, 000 poorly trained and ill-equipped Filipino army soldiers to defend the Philippines. <br/><br/>\r\n\r\n With MacArthur\'s forces retreating to Bataan on late December, 1941, and the fall of Manila on Jan 2 to the Japanese, President Roosevelt felt he could not afford to lose the general.', 'May the Philippines come up with better defense plan of its territory especially with the communist Chinese encroaching in on the West Philippine Sea and on other areas subtly. May the Armed Forces of the Philippines acquire better technology, weapons, ships, planes and training.', 'Do not conform to the pattern of this world, but be transformed by the renewing of your mind. <br/>\r\n–<b> Romans 12:2a</b>', '<i>In human history, we can see sparkles of God\'s redeeming stories</i><br/>\r\n- Pastor Jose Tacadena', 'https://bit.ly/2LY1rRv', 1, NULL, 'Just like Pres. Roosevelt and Gen. MacArthur, may we all learn to move out when needed. God Himself wants Christians to move out of the worldly system.'),
(166, '2021-02-24', '2021-02-24', 'On The Start Of The US Led Gulf War Ground Invasion of Kuwait and Iraq.', 'In 1991, the US-Led Gulf War ground invasion of Kuwait and Iraq began. <br/><br/>\r\n\r\n This was after six weeks after their intense Allied bombing against Iraq and its armed forces. The attack was authorized by the United Nations Security Council as Iraq, led by Saddam Hussein, refused to withdraw from Kuwait, which it annexed by force on August 2, 1990. <br/><br/>\r\n\r\n The ground attack was led by US General Norman Schwarzkopf and soldiers from 32 nations including Muslim nations.\r\n', 'May Iraq, Kuwait (and Syria) fully recover as individuals without becoming threats to peace and order in the Gulf. May invasion of a country be another be prevented by an alliance of nations.', 'For lack of guidance a nation falls, but victory is won through many advisers. <br/>\r\n- <b> Proverbs 11:14 </b>', '<i>In human history, we can see sparkles of God\'s redeeming stories</i><br/>\r\n- Pastor Jose Tacadena', 'https://bit.ly/3oe7Yoq', 0, NULL, 'It\'s noteworthy that though the US alone can take on Iraq with its military might, it didn\'t rush attacking it. After four days, Kuwait was liberated and Iraq surrendered.'),
(167, '2021-02-24', '2021-02-24', 'On Final Nails To Pres Marcos\' Political Career Being Hammered Through.', 'In 1986, the final nails to Pres. Marcos\' political career was said to have been hammered through. <br/><br/>\r\n\r\n First, the pilots of the Philippine Air Force choppers who were reportedly tasked to bomb Juan Ponce Enrile and Fidel Ramos\' group in Camp Crame defected to the rebels side. <br/><br/>\r\n\r\n The pilots even used the choppers to advance the cause of the Gen. Ramos later. Second, Ramos\' forces seized the government TV Station Channels 4, 7 and 9. This stopped the so-called propaganda machinery of the government and confirmed that the rebel soldiers were truly in control.\r\n', 'May any more attempt for military coup be prevented early on. May the Filipino soldiers stay loyal to the Constitution and the Filipino people, along with the principle of truth and justice.', 'Blessed are those whose help is the God of Jacob, whose hope is in the Lord their God. 6 He is the Maker of heaven and earth, the sea, and everything in them— he remains faithful forever. 7 He upholds the cause of the oppressed and gives food to the hungry. The Lord sets prisoners free. <br/>\r\n–<b> Psalm 146:5-7 </b>', '<i>In human history, we can see sparkles of God\'s redeeming stories</i><br/>\r\n- Pastor Jose Tacadena', 'https://bit.ly/39cl550', 1, NULL, 'At least two realities are manifested in this story <br/><br/>\r\n\r\n 1. Man\'s loyalty changes <br/><br/>\r\n\r\n 2. God\'s faithfulness is unchanging.'); 
INSERT INTO `glimpse` (`id`, `title`, `glimpse_date`, `heading`, `content`, `prayer_focus`, `featured_verse`, `featured_quote`, `image_link`, `type`, `created_at`, `transition`) VALUES
INSERT INTO `glimpse` (`id`, `title`, `glimpse_date`, `heading`, `content`, `prayer_focus`, `featured_verse`, `featured_quote`, `image_link`, `type`, `created_at`, `transition`) VALUES
(172, '2021-02-27', '2021-02-27', 'On The Ending Of Gulf War.', 'In 1991, the Gulf War, which began in August 2, 1990 with the Iraqi invasion of Kuwait, ended after 6 months, 3 weeks and 5 days. <br/><br/>\r\n\r\n This was after Saudi Forces entered Kuwait and officially liberate it from invading Iraq, and the 80, 000 Iraqi army that fled from it were captured by the Allied Forces led by the US. <br/><br/>\r\n\r\n Iraq announced later their unconditional acceptance of the UN Resolutions on Kuwait. Kuwaiti monarchy was restored, UN sanctions against Iraq was enforced and "no fly zone" in that country was established. US lost 184 lives, Iraq lost 85, 000. Iraq\'s infrastructures took $200 billion to repair while Kuwait lost $50 billion.', 'May Iraq recover economically without being a threat again in the region. May Kuwait continue to be independent. And may the coalition of nations maintain vigilance for the peace and order of the said region.', 'Or suppose a king is about to go to war against another king. Won\'t he first sit down and consider whether he is able with ten thousand men to oppose the one coming against him with twenty thousand? 32 If he is not able, he will send a delegation while the other is still a long way off and will ask for terms of peace. <br/>\r\n- <b> Luke 14:31-32 </b>', '<i>In human history, we can see sparkles of God\'s redeeming stories</i><br/>\r\n- Pastor Jose Tacadena', 'https://bit.ly/3qKmmq7', 0, NULL, 'May countries and their leaders avoid engaging in wars, realizing its fatal costs.'),
(173, '2021-02-27', '2021-02-27', 'On Gen. Douglas Restoring The Philippine Commonwealth In Behalf On The US Government.', 'In 1945, Gen. Douglas MacArthur restored the Philippine Commonwealth in behalf of the US government. <br/><br/>\r\n\r\n This was the culmination of the commonwealth restoration which started on October 23, 1944 in Tacloban, Leyte. This was shortly after MacArthur\'s return, with Sergio Osmeña as president. <br/><br/>\r\n\r\n During the ceremonies in Malacañang, Pres. Osmeña, by virtue of an executive order, restored all the executive departments of the government with certain modifications. He also declared that the judicial branch will be re-established immediately. <br/><br/>\r\n\r\n Finally, he called on the Congress to be ready to meet in Manila as soon as conditions allow for the re-establishment of the Legislative Branch.', 'May the Philippine government remain independent from manipulations by other countries. May our national leaders be truly God-fearing, nation-loving and technically equipped in their tasks.', 'He changes times and seasons; he deposes kings and raises up others. He gives wisdom to the wise and knowledge to the discerning. <br/>\r\n–<b> Daniel 2:21 </b>', '<i>In human history, we can see sparkles of God\'s redeeming stories</i><br/>\r\n- Pastor Jose Tacadena', 'https://bit.ly/3c7uIE5', 1, NULL, 'May we all vote wisely. May we all help in implementing fairness, justice and truth in our society.'),
(174, '2021-02-28', '2021-02-28', 'On James D. Watson And Francis H.C. Crick Discovering The Structure Of DNA.', 'In 1953, James D. Watson and Francis H.C Crick, Cambridge University scientists, discovered the structure of DNA, the molecule containing human genes. <br/><br/>\r\n\r\n They discovered that the deoxyribonucleic acid is a double-helix polymer, a spiral of two DNA strands, each containing along chain of monomer nucleotides, wound around each other. <br/><br/>\r\n\r\n This discovery revolutionized the study of biology and medicine. It includes the pre-natal screening for disease genes, genetically engineered foods and the rational design of treatments for disease, and the accurate testing of physical evidence to convict or exonerate criminals.', 'May more discoveries and inventions be made by our scientists and researchers for the improvement of medicines and health. May all the discoveries help us realize that God, who created us, is truly amazing and worth appreciating.', 'For you created my inmost being; you knit me together in my mother’s womb. 14 I praise You because I am fearfully and wonderfully made; Your works are wonderful,I know that full well. 15 My frame was not hidden from You when I was made in the secret place, when I was woven together in the depths of the earth. 16 Your eyes saw my unformed body; all the days ordained for me were written in your book before one of them came to be. <br/>\r\n- <b> Psalm 139:13-16 </b>', '<i>In human history, we can see sparkles of God\'s redeeming stories</i><br/>\r\n- Pastor Jose Tacadena', 'https://bit.ly/3og7wpJ', 0, NULL, 'This is what King David experienced.'),
(175, '2021-02-28', '2021-02-28', 'On Pres. Rodrigo Duterte Signing The Paris Agreement On Climate Change.', 'In 2017, Pres. Rodrigo Duterte signed the Paris agreement on Climate Change. <br/><br/>\r\n\r\n This was despite the president\'s initial declaration that he intended to pull the Philippines out of the pact, believing that the small countries would be disadvantaged by it. <br/><br/>\r\n\r\n The Paris Agreement\'s main aim is to strengthen the global response to the threat of the climate change by keeping a global temperature rise this century well below the 2 degrees Celsius above the pre-industrial levels. This in turn, is to pursue efforts to limit the temperature increase to 1.5 degrees Celsius. <br/><br/>\r\n\r\n The Philippines became the 138th state party to the agreement.', 'May this agreement on climate change be fulfilled to the letter by all state parties involved. May the Filipinos learn to truly practice pro-environmentalism and be held accountable for failures committed against the nature and environment.', 'The earth is defiled by its people; they have disobeyed the laws, violated the statutes and broken the everlasting covenant. 6 Therefore a curse consumes the earth; its people must bear their guilt. Therefore earth\'s inhabitants are burned up, and very few are left. <br/>\r\n–<b> Isaiah 24:5-6 </b>', '<i>In human history, we can see sparkles of God\'s redeeming stories</i><br/>\r\n- Pastor Jose Tacadena', 'https://bit.ly/3pdUU3y', 1, NULL, 'Do you know that even the Bible attests that the deterioration of the earth and the environment is caused by men themselves?');
